title: chinese style goulash
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Cook and stir onion and mushrooms in butter until onion is tender.
Add chicken broth and heat to boiling.
Stir in rice and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes; stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: green beans in mushroom sauce
directions: Drain green beans.
Heat mushroom soup in large pan; add beans and onions.
Simmer until well heated.
Add sherry; serve topped with almonds.
Yields 24 servings.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Place balls in greased tart pans.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven.
Push miniature Reese's cup in cookie.
Let cool slightly.
Remove from pans.

title: 'possum 'n' taters
directions: Clean 'possum and cook in salted water until tender. Meanwhile, bake potatoes until soft.
Peel and quarter them lengthwise. Place cooked 'possum and potatoes in baking dish.
Dot with butter. Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: golden apple crunch
directions: Pare, core and slice apples.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, cloves and lemon juice.
Mix into apples.
Turn into 8x8 baking dish or 6 cup casserole.

title: dynamite sauce
directions: Brown hamburg.
Slice peppers and onions.
Microwave to soften.
Slice mushrooms and minced garlic.

title: black forrest dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in a greased 2-quart rectangular glass pan. Spread chocolate chips over top.
Spread cake mix evenly over chips.
Slice butter lengthwise in four pieces and spread evenly over dry batter.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt in first bowl.
Cream together in large, second bowl, the margarine and sugar, then add beaten eggs.
Then add mashed bananas.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Then add walnuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Blend all ingredients (except coconut) in blender, covered, at low speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 or 10-inch pie plate (glass preferred) or two (8-inch) plates for 2 pies (increase baking time by 20 minutes or so if metal pans are used).
Sprinkle coconut on top, pat down with back of large spoon and let stand 5 minutes.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes its own crust.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash relish
directions: Cut all vegetables in small pieces or grind.
Soak in 1/2 gallon water and 3/4 cup salt for 1 hour.
After soaking, drain well and dry on towel.
Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed and celery seed in saucepan; let come to a boil.
Add vegetables; let come to a boil.
Pack in glass jars and seal.

title: burger pizza
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, onion, egg and salt. Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press meat mixture evenly over bottom of 12-inch pizza pan.
Form 1/2-inch rim around edge.
Spread pizza sauce over meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheeses and choice of pizza toppers over sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Drain off excess fat.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Yields one 12-inch pizza.

title: salmon potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first seven ingredients. Add salmon; toss lightly. In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, garlic salt and lemon-pepper seasoning; mix well. Pour over the salad and stir gently. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Yield: 8 servings.

title: cheesy cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese very fine.
Cream cheese with butter; add flour, paprika and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll dough on floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in strips about 1/2-inch wide and 4 inches long or may be pressed through a pastry tube.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Do not brown.
Makes about 7 dozen sticks.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Put one layer of cake in the bottom of the bowl.
Cover with vanilla pudding.
Place strawberries on top with juice.
Add a sprinkle of almonds.
Follow with a second cake layer, pudding and strawberries.
Top with whipped topping; decorate with strawberries and almonds.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Then heat liquid to a good, hard boil. Boil for 5 minutes.
Pack in sterile jars.

title: fudge sundae ice cream pie
directions: Mix on medium heat until thick.
Take off heat and let cool. Line bottom of 8-inch pie pan with whole vanilla wafers.
Spoon in a layer of vanilla ice cream; spoon a layer of fudge sauce. Repeat ice cream and chocolate until out of sauce.
Place in freezer.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: coney island hot dog sauce(at nathan's stand)
directions: Put meat in pan, cover with water (on medium heat).
Bring to simmer mash with potato masher until very fine.
Add paprika, chili powder, cumin and salt.
Simmer 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix and spread on cake.

title: freckle face pancakes
directions: Beat with rotary beater in a medium bowl until smooth the first three ingredients. Then fold in 1/2 cup of cranberry sauce. Drizzle a small amount of batter from a teaspoon onto hot griddle to make funny eyes, nose and mouth.
When they puff up, pour about 1/4 cup of butter over them.
Turn when bubbles appear.
Bake other side until golden brown.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add chili powder and garlic salt. Layer pan with Doritos, beans and meat.
Mix soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes and pour over top.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Cook celery in margarine for a few minutes.
Stir in flour and blend thoroughly.
Stir in broth and milk and cook until smooth and thick.
Season to taste with salt.
Add chicken and heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: orange angel fluff
directions: Cook eggs, sugar and orange juice over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in orange peel and cool. Prepare topping mix as directed on package except substitute skim milk for the milk. Fold orange mixture into topping. Refrigerate 1 hour before serving. Refrigerate any leftover topping. Serve 2 tablespoons orange topping per slice of Orange Sponge Cake.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve chilled.

title: citrus pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugar and butter well with the zest added at the end. Slowly add eggs two by two, then add in the fresh squeezed juice. Then add in flavoring. Mix in flour and baking powder until incorporated. To finish, place in baking pan and bake at 300° for 15 minutes. Makes 30 mini pound cakes.

title: hildegarde aiken's cry baby cookies 2
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add beaten eggs, then molasses, then milk. Sift dry ingredients together and gradually add to first mixture. Add floured raisins last.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake in slow oven (325° to 350°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen cookies.

title: graham wafers("these are wholesome and good for the children.")
directions: "A careful observance of these little occurrences... lies within the province, and indeed should be considered among the highest duties, of every housekeeper."

title: herb chicken
directions: Combine flour, sage and thyme; coat chicken lightly.
In skillet over medium-high heat, melt margarine.
Cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides; push chicken to one side. Stir in soup and water, stirring to loosen browned bits.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes, or until chicken is fork-tender.
Serve over rice.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Trim separable fat from veal steak.
Cut veal into 4 pieces; pound to 1/8-inch thickness.
Spray a cold 12-inch skillet with nonstick coating.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Cook veal in hot skillet for 2 to 3 minutes or until no longer pink, turning once.
Remove from skillet; cover with foil to keep warm.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package directions.
Chill until slightly set.
Stir in Cool Whip, celery, pineapple and chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Core and dice apples.
In a large bowl of mixer, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
In bowl, sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine egg and flour mixtures.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Batter will be thick. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, blend oil and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
In another bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and oats and add them to the mixture.
Add optional ingredients if desired.
Shape into small balls and flatten onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: potato kugel
directions: Grate potatoes and small onion fine.
Saute large onion in fat. Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart Pyrex casserole.
Bake at 375° until brown and crusty on top, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 10.

title: hot clam dip(serve with crackers)
directions: Saute onion in butter.
In a separate bowl, mix bread crumbs, diced Mozzarella, lemon juice and clams with juice.
Add garlic, parsley and oregano to onion while cooking.
Mix and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour onion into bowl with clams.
Cook in casserole 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
When brown on top, it's finished.

title: man's best burger
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide into 4 parts.
Grill on medium heat until done.
Butter 4 buns and place on grill for 1 minute.
Top with lettuce, tomato, red onion and bacon.
Enjoy!

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sugar with pineapple, undrained.
Heat until sugar is dissolved. Pour over cake while hot.
Cook pudding as directed.
Pour over cake.
Cool; spread with Cool Whip, then top with coconut.
Must refrigerate overnight.
Have all ingredients at room temperature before making cake.

title: cranberry ham
directions: Place ham in greased casserole.
Spoon cranberry sauce evenly over ham.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cloves.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water and salt.
Cool slightly.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Melt oleo; add flour and mustard to it, then add this mixture to warm grits.
Add 2 cups grated cheese; stir.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and cover with the remaining cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sausage cheese grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 3-quart dish; set aside. Bring water and salt to a boil in large saucepan. Slowly stir in grits. Cook 4 to 5 minutes; stir occasionally. Remove from heat. Stir small amount grits mix into eggs. Return all to saucepan. Add sausage, 1 cup cheese, milk and water; blend well. Pour into prepared baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake 1 hour or until cheese is golden brown. Let cool 10 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: specially good quick stew
directions: Brown onion in drippings.
Add meat and brown, tossing to keep it separated.
Add salt.
Stir in spaghetti.
Combine soup, grated cheese and pickle relish.
Heat until cheese is melted, then stir into meat mixture.

title: 7-up mold
directions: Mix lime Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix in cream cheese and beat with hand mixer.
Add pineapple with juice, 7-Up and vanilla. Pour into a large mold.
Allow to set until firm and serve.

title: real italian lasagne
directions: Brown garlic and green pepper in oil.
Add tomatoes, sauce and spices; cook 45 to 60 minutes.
Brown hamburger, add to first mixture, then cook another 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed (glob of oil in water keeps noodles from sticking). Rotate in casserole dish:
sauce mix, noodles, sauce, noodles, cheeses, sauce, noodles, cheeses; finish with cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until cheese melts.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions and refrigerate until syrupy.
Whip and add Cool Whip and strawberries, including liquid.
Tear cake into bite-sized pieces and place half in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Pour half the strawberry mixture over the cake; repeat layers.
Refrigerate.

title: grandma warner's amish-style macaroni salad
directions: Mix together.
Add dressing, garnish and refrigerate.
Best if refrigerated for 6 hours before serving.

title: punch for twenty-five
directions: Mix and keep refrigerated until time to serve or in the freezer if you want it real icy.
Add 1 quart of ginger ale at serving time.

title: quiche
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into greased quiche dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: quick beans for a crowd
directions: Heat oil in extra deep, 12 inch nonstick skillet on med-low. Peel and finely chop onion adding to skillet as you chop.
Seed and finely chop pepper, adding as you chop.
Raise heat to med-hi and cook 5 minutes or until onion is tender.

title: rotini antipasto salad
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions; drain.
In large bowl, combine rotini and next seven ingredients.
In small bowl, whisk together next five ingredients.
Pour dressing over pasta mixture; toss to coat.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, add olives and toss gently.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: al's chili
directions: Brown the beef; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Can also be cooked in a crock-pot, low 10 to 12 hours, high 5 to 6 hours.

title: vegetable-stuffed squash
directions: Wash squash thoroughly and place in a large saucepan.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 6 minutes. Drain and cool slightly.
Trim off stems and cut squash in half lengthwise; gently scoop out pulp, leaving a firm shell.
Drain and chop pulp; combine pulp and remaining ingredients.
Place squash shells in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; spoon vegetable mixture into shells.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lettuce salad
directions: In large bowl, chop lettuce.
Add grated Parmesan cheese and toasted sesame seed.
Pour Seasons Italian dressing on top and lightly mix.
Chill.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and dice eggplant.
Cook in water until tender; drain. Mash eggplant with potato masher and add salt and black pepper.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Crumble cake into a 9X13 inch dish. In a medium bowl, cream sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy. Fold in whipped topping. Mash cake down with your hands and spread cream cheese mixture over cake. In a bowl, combine strawberries and glaze until strawberries are evenly coated. Spread over cream cheese layer. Chill until ready to serve.

title: layered spaghetti casserole
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Set beef aside.

title: mississippi lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, corn meal and salt.
Add butter, lemon juice, lemon rind and milk; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Yield: 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and cut in large pieces.
Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Put this in bottom of large baking dish.
Place chicken chunks on top.
Sprinkle salt and pepper to taste.
Mix can of cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with grated cheese and 1/4 cup bread chunks.
Dot with margarine.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: bacon wrap arounds
directions: Cut bacon slices in half; wrap around pineapple chunks or water chestnuts.
Broil long enough to get fat out, but not crisp. Broil far from broiler flame. Watch closely and turn.
Pour off fat.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over wrap arounds. Bake at 300° with sauce on for about 30 minutes.

title: ground beef stroganoff(quick, easy and yummy!)
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and garlic. Add mushrooms and mushroom soup and bring to boil.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly but avoid burning.
Serve over wide egg noodles.

title: easy oven lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and salt. Bring to a boil.
In a 2-quart baking dish, layer the hot sauce, lasagna noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers ending with sauce.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream butter, sugar, cream cheese and vanilla together.
Add nuts.
Spread on cake.

title: navajo frybread
directions: Enough warm water or milk to make a soft dough.
Mix ingredients and knead the resulting dough for about 10 minutes (while oil is heating to a smoking hot).
Hand pat into thin, flat circles the size of a pancake.
Keep submerged in deep hot oil until brown.
Serve at once.
Add honey, if desired.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald 2 cups milk. Remove from heat and add 1 cup shortening and 1 cup sugar. Let cool. Dissolve 1 package yeast in 1 cup warm water. Add to milk mixture when cool.

To this add enough flour to make soft batter. Let rise until double, then add 2 cups flour, 1 1/2 heaping teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon baking powder and a scant 1/2 teaspoon soda. Mix well and refrigerate in large covered container.
Make rolls as needed. Will keep in refrigerator approximately 2 weeks or make out and freeze. Makes approximately 42 rolls.

title: coconut creme pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in pan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Stir 1/2 of hot mixture in egg yolks.
Blend all.
Boil 1 minute longer.
Blend in butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour in cooled pie crust.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a new flowerpot (8 x 10-inch), silk flowers and candy gummy worms

title: pam's famous no guilt low-fat mud pie
directions: Crush SnackWell's graham snacks with a rolling pin on waxed paper.
In a large bowl, blend graham crackers, sugar, Nestle Quik and liquid Butter Buds.
Press this mixture into a deep dish pie pan that has been sprayed with nonfat vegetable cooking spray. Pour softened frozen yogurt into the crust.
Place in freezer for at least 1 hour.
Once the yogurt has hardened, you may spread the fudge topping on top of it.
Place the pie back in the freezer for 30 minutes.

title: after holiday casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions on box, adding minced onion to boiling water.
Fluff rice with a fork and spread in a 1 1/2-quart utility dish.
Defrost peas and drain.
Sprinkle peas and green pepper over rice.
Cover with turkey.
(You may break turkey into small pieces or leave in slices.
Chicken can be used.)
Mix soup with milk and pour over turkey.
Combine crumbs with butter and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Cover dish with plastic film and cook in microwave oven for 12 minutes, turning dish every 3 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: sweet and sour meatloaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Line the bottom with greased wax paper.
Whip eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in pineapple, ketchup, brown sugar, mustard, salt, garlic, and pepper.
Stir in bread crumbs, onion, and half the meat until thoroughly blended.
Work in remaining meat and press into pan. Lay a sheet of tin foil loosely over meat and bake for 1 hour. Uncover and drain off fat, continue baking uncovered for 30 - 40 min.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Stir together thoroughly flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt. Cream the oleo, shortening, white sugar and powdered sugar together.
Add dry ingredients slowly to creamed ingredients.
Add egg, vanilla and almond.
Make into small balls.
Press down with a buttered glass (take one with a decorative pattern on bottom).
Dip glass into sugar before pressing down onto cookie.

title: texas stuffed pepper
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef; drain off drippings.
Add onions, salt, pepper and sage; cook thoroughly.
In small bowl, mix hot sauce, tomato sauce and tomato paste with 1 cup water. Add half of sauce mixture to ground beef; cook slowly.
Add rice. Cut out (from the top) bell pepper and wash thoroughly.
With a spoon, stuff green pepper with mixture, letting overflow just a little.
Bake at 350° in oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Crumble crackers or cornflakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zesty punch sipper
directions: Combine all ingredients in large punch bowl or two large pitchers.
Makes 20 servings.

title: gourmet tuna salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers or sandwich bread (may be toast) on lettuce.

title: latkes
directions: In a large bowl, mix the egg and grated potatoes.
Add flour and baking powder.
Drop by spoonful into hot cooking oil in a frying pan.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on a paper towel.
Serve with applesauce or sour cream.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare icing first and refrigerate while baking cake.
Mix Cool Whip and instant pudding and then add crushed pineapple and juice.
Refrigerate.

title: apple pie in a scoop
directions: In large
pan, combine sugar, flour and milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Stir 1 cup of batter into eggs;
return all to pan. Cook
and
stir
2 more minutes.
Cover and chill 1/2 hour.
Stir in cream, pie filling, vanilla and cinnamon.
Put in 4
or	5 quart
ice cream freezer and follow directions on freezer for making ice cream.

title: stuffed kibbeh
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients very well and grind again.
Soften the mixture by adding 2 or 3 tablespoons ice water and kneading it well.
Let rest in the refrigerator.

title: ginger molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, cloves, ginger, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Melt shortening over water and cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix. Chill.
Roll into balls.
Roll in sugar.
Do not flatten.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fish stew
directions: Fry bacon in bottom of 10-quart pot.
Add fish, potatoes, and onions in alternating layers.
Add tomato paste and sausage if desired.
Add seasonings.
Cover with water and cook 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve with cornbread or loaf bread.

title: salmonettes
directions: Drain fish into measuring cup.
Flake fish in a bowl. Add egg and mix with fork. Add flour and mix again. Add pepper.
Use 1/4 cup liquid and mix with baking powder.
Let foam until it reaches 3/4 cup mark.
Mix into
fish mixture.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Turn once.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place the potatoes in a boiler.
Add the ground beef, butter beans, okra and onion.
Add enough water to cover good.
Add the rice and mix all ingredients.
Cook over low heat until tender, then add the tomatoes.
Cook until well done.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Serve with cream cheese and
Ritz
crackers.
The
sauce can be put on top of a block
of cream cheese.
Sauce is also good with meat and can be
used on bread instead of mayonnaise.
Sauce can be refrigerated
up
to several months.
You can also substitute peach preserves or use 12 ounces of preserves instead of 18 ounces.

title: radish and onion spread
directions: Mix together with softened cream cheese.
Great with crackers or chips.

title: quick skillet dinner
directions: Mix together and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: date logs
directions: Put nuts and dates through a food chopper (using coarse side). Mix nuts and dates with 1 1/2 cups of coconut, sugar and eggs. Shape mixture into rolls about 3/4-inch thick and 2-inches long. Roll logs into remaining 1/2 cup of coconut.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° until lightly brown.

title: hash brown casserole number 1
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese and salt. Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°. (Let potatoes thaw before baking.)

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and salt.
Add egg, oil and milk. Coat each dog with flour and insert onto wooden skewer.
Dip into corn meal mix and coat all sides. Fry a few at a time in deep fat 375 F until golden brown.

title: man's cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg and vanilla, then dry ingredients, then coconut, nuts and oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: microwave pecan pralines
directions: In
medium
glass
bowl, combine sugars, corn syrup and water; heat
to
9 minutes on High until mixture reads 238° (soft ball
stage)
when
tested
with
a
candy thermometer. Important: Do not use candy thermometer in dish while operating
the microwave oven.
Stir in pecans, butter and vanilla. Let
stand 2 minutes.
Drop by tablespoonful onto well-greased wax paper lined cookie
sheet; chill until set.
Yields about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugar in a mixer bowl at high speed until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs, 1 at a time.
Blend in sour cream.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Note:
Freeze steak 1 hour to make slicing easier.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Add onions and cook until lightly brown. Add potatoes and stir.
Heat thoroughly.
Empty this in greased casserole dish.
Mix with soup and sour cream, salt and pepper. Add to potatoes.
Cover top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Add onion rings and bake 10 minutes more with lid.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into two floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes.
Place tomatoes in a deep dish.
Combine all other ingredients; pour over tomatoes.
Chill overnight.

title: spaghetti sauce (school)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until hot.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: Up to one hour before serving, mix coleslaw, onion, almonds and sunflower kernels in a bowl.
In a jar, combine oil, vinegar, sugar, pepper and Oriental seasoning pack.
Cover.
Shake and chill.
At serving time, add the Ramen noodles (broken up) to salad mix and pour dressing over top.
Toss to coat and serve.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients, blending thoroughly at medium speed.

title: easy enchilada pie
directions: In large skillet, brown lean ground beef and onion; drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Bring the mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat, simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Remove the skillet from the heat.
Stir together the condensed soup and milk.
Spoon half the soup mixture into a 13x9x2 inch pan.
Cut the tortillas in half.
Use 12 halves to place over soup in pan.
Spoon meat mixture over tortillas.
Top with remaining tortillas.
Spoon remaining soup mixture over the tortillas.
Top with cheese.
Bake casserole in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: stewed cabbage and carrots
directions: Put cabbage, carrots and butter into medium pot.
Cover cabbage with cold water.
Cook over medium heat until juice is almost gone. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: burger mushroom bake
directions: Combine 1/2 cup soup with remaining ingredients, except water. Mix, shape into 6 oval patties.
Place in shallow dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese patties
directions: Mix well and fry in oil.
Place in deep casserole pan and pour mushroom soup over.
Simmer in oven for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: basic light brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and water.
Mix well. Sift together dry ingredients and add to wet mixture.
Mix well. Stir in ingredients from any variation below.
Drop in walnut size lumps onto greased cookie sheet and bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields at least 3 dozen.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Chill evaporated milk in freezer tray until crystals form around edge.
Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water; chill until partially thickened.
Beat cheese well with a fork; add sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Whip chilled milk until stiff.
Fold in gelatin and then cheese mixture.
Mix butter with graham cracker crumbs; spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan and pour mixture over this. Yield:
12 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on pizza pan and bake until brown.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing mix.
Spread on crust.	Add chopped vegetables on top:	cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, celery, pepper, tomatoes and grated cheese (include or delete any vegetables you like).

title: chili pie
directions: Brown meat.
Mix everything except cheedar & chips.
Layer meat mixture with chips.
Sprinkle cheddar on top.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover for last 10 minutes.

title: beer muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease muffin pan. Mix all ingredients until smooth. Pour in muffin cups. Bake 15 minutes.

title: light and easy lemon broccoli chicken
directions: In hot oil in skillet,	cook
chicken
ten
minutes
or until browned on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Combine soup and milk. Stir in lemon juice and
pepper.
Pour over chicken and top each piece of chicken with slice
of lemon.
Reheat on low (covered) 5 minutes or until
chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally. Serves 4.
Ready in fifteen minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth; set aside.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans; set aside.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of sugar mixture over batter.
Repeat procedure.
Gently swirl batter with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clear.
Drizzle glaze over cool cake.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Add applesauce and raisins.
Sift dry ingredients together and fold in nuts.
Bake in 9-inch square pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee icing
directions: Mix softened butter with coffee. Add confectioners sugar while mixing. Continue until icing is thick enough to spread.

title: chocolate cherries
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese, vanilla, and salt by hand.
Roll into balls.
Put hole in center with thumb.
Put cherry into center and roll again.
Place on waxed paper and chill.

title: carrot fritters
directions: Sift flour, then add salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add carrots, using just enough milk to soften enough to drop from spoon.
Fry in deep fat, turning over a few times, until golden brown.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Cook noodles in broth; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 450° until cheese is melted.

title: sally's cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add the peanut butter and rolled oats.
Stir together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let them cool.
Do not bake.

title: pumpkin gems
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Fill mini muffin papers 2/3 full.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool, then frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: fried oysters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Stir milk in mixture to make a thin batter.
Add the oysters, without liquor, to batter and stir.
Heat the oil in frying pan.
When hot, spoon oysters individually with generous amount of batter.
Fry oysters on both sides until golden brown.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; slice and put in a heavy pan of water.
Cover with the salt.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Pour water off; almost cover with fresh water.
Add the sugar.
Cook until it turns light in color and syrup is done.

title: banana nut chocolate chip bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large bowl, cream butter or margarine with sugar.
Add beaten eggs and milk to sugar mixture. Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Combine with sugar mixture.
Blend in vanilla extract and smashed bananas, mix well.

title: diabetic date nut loaf
directions: Cream butter and egg.
Add sweetener and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add dates and nuts.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: savory glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Defrost broccoli and drain well.
Mix in large
bowl all of the ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased pan and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: In small casserole dish, combine all ingredients.
Double this recipe when making a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
(When doubling, only use 1 stick margarine.)
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: crunch sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut biscuits in half.
Roll each half into 4-inch pencil like stick.
Brush with milk.
Mix cereal crumbs, seed and 1 teaspoon salt in shallow pan (be sure salt is well distributed).
Roll sticks in mixture.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes 20.

title: boiled chocolate icing
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil for 2 minutes.
Turn off eye and let mixture cool some.
Then beat well and put on cake.

title: mother's johnnycake
directions: Mix all together and put in muffin tins or 7 x 10-inch pan. Cook in 350° to 400° oven until done.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Cook the lasagna noodles.
Brown beef and garlic in salad oil. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, cheese and spices.
Cover and let simmer 15 minutes. Add layer of noodles and then meat mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook together chicken, salt, peppercorns, water, onion, 3 carrots, and 3 celery stalks until chicken is tender.
Discard onion, peppercorns, carrots and celery.
Debone chicken and chill. Cut chicken into small pieces.
Stir broth to remove all fat. Cook 3 carrots and 3 stalks celery in water and drain.
Combine broth, chicken and vegetables.
Season with cream of chicken soup, stick of butter, rice or dumplings.
Add milk, salt and pepper. Put in quart jars and seal.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Thinly slice 2 lemons.
In 1 1/2-quart pitcher, combine lemon slices and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press the fruit with potato masher or wooden spoon to release juice.
Cut and squeeze remaining lemons to get 2/3 cup lemon juice.
Pour juice into the pitcher with cold water and stir.
Taste, add more sugar, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add flour if mixture is running. Fry at least 10 minutes on each side.
After cooking, they can be frozen.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done, but firm.
Cut into bite-size pieces; mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Cool in refrigerator before serving.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Lay chops in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour orange juice over chops until covered.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: elephant ears
directions: Soften and dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Divide dough into 12 pieces.
Let set for 20 minutes.
Roll out on lightly floured board.
Stack with wax paper between each.

title: honey pancakes
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine milk and remaining ingredients; add to flour mixture, stirring until smooth.
For each pancake, pour approximately 1/4 cup batter onto hot, lightly greased griddle.
Turn with spatula when tops are bubbly and edges look cooked.
Yield:
28 (4-inch) pancakes, 92 calories each.

title: peach dessert
directions: Trim crust from angel food cake and tear into bite-sized pieces.
Beat instant pudding mix with milk and stir in yogurt.

title: halibut olympia
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add onion and green pepper. Place fillets on top of onion.
Cover fillets with 1/8-inch of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt, dill weed and paprika. Add bread crumbs and drizzle with melted butter.

title: cheddar cheese olive balls
directions: Knead all ingredients (except olives) together.
Form 48 small balls.
Make thumb imprint in each and insert olive in center, covering ball.
Freeze.
Bake frozen at 400° for 10 to 13 minutes until lightly browned.
Do not overcook.

title: oven french fries
directions: Combine cheese and oregano.
Cut potatoes into wedges, unpeeled.
Dip each wedge into egg, then into cheese.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain.
Return to pot.
Drain liquid from whole tomatoes into pot with macaroni.
Cut up tomatoes into small pieces.
Add to macaroni.
Stir gently.
In ovensafe casserole, layer macaroni-tomato mixture with slices of Swiss cheese.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add onion; brown.
Add beef; cook until redness is gone.
Add salt, pepper, mushrooms, flour and soup; stir and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Serve on rice.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix sugar with flour and water.
Melt oleo (let cool); mix. Add egg and remaining water and yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 275° for 15 minutes.

title: sunday roast
directions: Place roast in deep roasting pan, fat side up.
Puncture meat with meat fork.
Pour vinegar over.
Let stand 15 minutes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add water to pan.
Cover and bake at 400° for 3 1/2 hours or until
meat is tender, adding additional water if needed.
About 15 minutes before meat is done, uncover to brown the top.
Skim fat from pan.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter or margarine over medium heat.
Add orzo; cook until lightly browned, stirring constantly.
Stir in rice.
Add chicken broth, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Sprinkle with pine nuts before serving.

title: brazilian coffee(serves 1)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on medium speed for about 30 seconds.
Serve in chilled glass.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Bake potatoes (or microwave them until done), let them cool, then chop them up into bite sized cubes.
Mix potatoes and all other ingredients together and put in oven-safe casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab-rice salad
directions: In large bowl, toss cold rice, Old Bay and parsley, then drizzle French dressing and toss.
Fold in olives, celery, pineapple, crab and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate.
Serve on green lettuce leaves.

title: sauerkraut roast
directions: Put apple slices in crock-pot.
Cut roast in half and put on top of apples.
Mix other ingredients, except gravy mix, and pour over meat.
Cook on low 8 hours or until done.
Then stir in gravy mix.
Cover and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve over hot mashed potatoes with fresh carrots on the side.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Sauce:
Brown onion and garlic in 5 tablespoons of olive oil. Add rest of ingredients (except ground chuck) plus 1 tomato paste can of water.
Fry the ground chuck; drain.
Add to sauce and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: cheese vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and onions until tender.
Drain.
Toss vegetables with 2 tablespoons of Fryin Magic.
Melt cream cheese and garlic powder in saucepan over low heat.
Mix vegetables and cream cheese mixture together.
Put in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Mix 2 tablespoons Fryin Magic, bread crumbs, cheese and butter. Place on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Ingredients can be doubled for larger casserole.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Seal edges. Bake according to directions.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley mix.
Spread mix on cooled rolls. Put veggies on top (whichever you prefer): sliced mushrooms, tomatoes, green onions, broccoli, black olives, green pepper and lettuce.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cut into squares and serve from pan.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Half cup of flour may be substituted for cocoa for yellow cake, if desired.

title: fresh rhubarb bake
directions: Combine rhubarb and 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
Cream shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar, egg, cinnamon and salt.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add rhubarb mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Best if served warm with ice cream!

title: baked chicken with barbecue sauce
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil. Simmer 15 minutes.
Set aside.
Place chicken breasts in baking pan and cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove foil and pour sauce over chicken breasts.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Remove cover and cook an additional 40 minutes or until chicken is completely done.

title: chicken parmesan casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken until done.
Cube chicken into bite size pieces.
In another pot, heat up spaghetti sauce and add chicken pieces.
Simmer together for 15 minutes.
Cook elbow macaroni until done.
Mix cheeses together in a bowl.
Stir 1/2 of the cheese into chicken/sauce mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese mixture on the top.
Bake in oven for 15 minutes or until done (cheese will become brown and crispy).
Remove from oven and let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Process until smooth on high.
Makes 4 servings.

title: seasoned rice
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter until onions are tender but not brown.
Add rice, broth and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; stir once.
Cover and simmer for 14 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.
Serves 6.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Cut thin horizontal slice from bottom of watermelon so it will rest evenly; slice watermelon lengthwise in half. Carve a decorative zigzag edge from sliced edge of one-half of watermelon; scoop out fruit to form a bowl. Scoop melon balls from second half.

title: spaghetti with shrimp and fresh basil
directions: In dutch oven, over medium heat, cook onion and garlic in 1 Tbsp. butter until tender. Cook and stir for 1 minute. Stir in vermouth. Cook 8 minutes or until mixture is reduced by 1/3. Stir in Roux and tomato paste; cook 5 minutes.

title: banana sour cream bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Grease four 7 X 3 inch loaf pans.
In a small bowl, stir together 1/4 c. white sugar and cinnamon.
Dust pans lightly with cinnamon sugar mixture.
In a large bowl, cream butter and 3 c. sugar.
Mix in eggs, mashed bananas, sour cream, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix in salt, baking soda and flour.
Stir in nuts.
Divide into prepared pans.
Bake for 1 hour, until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: country coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.

Add remaining ingredients. Beat well. Reserve 1 cup of batter. Spread remaining batter in greased or pan sprayed jelly roll pan. Spread pie filling on batter. Drop remaining batter on top of filling. Carefully spread (with spatula) batter so that the drops slightly touch. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. You can check top with toothpick in center of pan for doneness. Let cool.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook hamburger; drain off fat.
Mix mushroom soup with hamburger.
Put layer of hamburger mixture on bottom of pan, corn in the middle, then mashed potatoes on top.
Make as many layers as desired.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°

title: halupki casserole
directions: Simmer cabbage and onion in pot of lightly salted water until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Mix diced tomatoes and tomato soup. Set aside.
Mix ground beef, rice, small onion and pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Take half of the tomato mixture and spoon on bottom of 9x13 inch pan.
Take half of the cabbage mixture and layer on top of tomato mixture.
Take spoonfuls of beef mixture and place on top of cabbage.
Use all of it.
Don't pat down.
Top meat with remainder of cabbage.
Top remainder of tomato mixture on top of cabbage.
Top with drained sauerkraut.
Pour sauerkraut juice on top.
Add enough water to come within 1/2 inch of the top of pan.
Cover with foil and bake for no less than 1 hour at 350°. Let sit for awhile before serving.
This is even better the next day.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Melt
chocolate
and
butter in saucepan over low heat; cool slightly.
Beat
eggs
slightly,
then gradually beat in sugar and continue
beating
for
to
3 minutes.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Stir in flour, then add vanilla and nuts. Spread in
a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about 30 to
35 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares or bars.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: cool carrots
directions: Cook carrots until barely done.
Cool.	Then combine all other ingredients.

title: strawberry pretzel
directions: Cream 3/4 cup oleo with 6 Tbsp. brown sugar.
Cook a few minutes.
Mix with crushed pretzels.
Pat into a buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: ham balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix the beef, ham, eggs and cracker crumbs until well blended.
Shape into balls. Place on a large, rimmed baking sheet.
In a separate bowl, stir together the remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour over ham balls.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 60 balls.

title: peach fluff(congealed salad)
directions: Drain all fruit well.
Cut up peaches into small pieces.
Mix jello and fruit until well blended, then add Cool Whip and pecans. Place in serving dish and chill at least 4-6 hours.

title: peach, cantaloupe, pineapple jam
directions: Wash and prepare fruit.
Place fruit in kettle (large one). Add lemon juice and pectin.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar.
Cook for 1 minute.
Pour into jelly jars.
Skim off foam first.
Seal. Place in hot water to cover jars and process for 5 minutes.
Keeps real well for 1 year.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream all cheeses together (may have to mix with hands).
Add a few nuts and onion.
Mix well.
Keep adding a few at a time (save some to roll in).
Add horseradish and sauce; mix well. Roll in ball and put in refrigerator.
When firm, roll in remainder of nuts.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Just before cake comes out of the oven, dissolve orange jello in boiling water. When cake is baked, with meat fork, pierce holes in hot cake to the bottom of the pan.
Pour hot, dissolved jello over hot cake gently.
Put in fridge to set and cool.
When cold, spread with frosting.

title: "yummy" vanilla pudding dessert
directions: Blend the pudding and milk together until thick and smooth. Set aside, then blend together powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla flavoring.
Put this in the pudding mix.
Fold in the whip cream until creamy, soft and smooth.
Take the cookies apart and scrape the cream out with a knife.
Put cookies in a plastic bag and crush them until fine.
Then put cookies in the bottom of the pan.
Pour the smooth batter over the cookies.
Leave some of the cookie crumbs for the top.
Sprinkle on top and then chill for a while.
Take out and enjoy.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Break half the bread into pieces and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (greased with Pam).
Mix sugar and cinnamon, then sprinkle 1/2 of the mixture on bread.
Break second half of bread into pieces and place on the first layer.
Sprinkle the rest of the sugar and cinnamon on the bread.
Melt the margarine and pour over the bread.
Cover the rolls and let them rise for 2 hours. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn over onto a cookie sheet and cool.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Put in baked 9-inch pie shell.
Add meringue on top. Brown in oven.

title: coconut and cherry drops
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Set aside. Cream butter and sugar. Add egg and almond extract to sugar mixture. Add dry ingredients. Mix thoroughly. Add cherries, nuts and coconut. Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet. Top with a cherry. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: beef noodle stroganoff
directions: In skillet, cook beef and garlic until browned.
Drain and stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Place noodles in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with meat mixture.
In a small bowl, mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth; stir in onions.
Spread over meat mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 30 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Beat eggs with milk.
Salt and pepper steaks and roll in eggs; dip in flour.
Get grease hot and brown steaks on both sides.
Put in large pan or Pyrex dish.
Pour soup over steaks.
Put in 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes and vegetables.

title: bugs on a toilet seat
directions: Cut 1 small apple in half and core.
On one-half, spread 1 tablespoon of peanut butter.
Decorate with 1 tablespoon of raisins.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: brown betty
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar on the top.
Over this, pour the boiling water.
Dot with butter and bake approximately 40 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles.
Brown meat and add spaghetti sauce. Put a couple of spoonfuls of meat sauce on bottom of baking dish. Layer as follows:
Meat sauce, Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Finish with meat sauce and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Can freeze for future use.
When frozen, bake at 425° for 1 hour and 55 minutes.
If defrosted before baking, bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: deviled pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops and put in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chops. Bake in a 400° oven about 45 minutes or until tender.

title: not yo' mama's banana pudding
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13 dish with 1 bag of cookies and layer bananas on top.

title: hawaiian sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Arrange a layer of sliced potatoes in a buttered 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar, dot with a tablespoon of butter.
Top this layer with a layer of bananas.
Repeat layers, using remaining potatoes, bananas, brown sugar and butter.
Pour orange juice over all.
Sprinkle with coconut and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until top is brown.
Serve hot.

title: crispie barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg, 3/4 cup Rice Krispies, salt, pepper and onion; mix well.
In small bowl, mix brown sugar, catsup, nutmeg and mustard.
Put 1/2 of this mixture into beef mixture; mix well. Shape into small meatballs and place on rack on top of cookie sheet.
Put remaining catsup and mixture on top of meatballs. Sprinkle remaining Rice Krispies over top of meatballs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: apple-cabbage slaw
directions: Pour fruit juices over apples.
Add cabbage and mix lightly. Mix mayo, applesauce, horseradish and mustard.
Pour over apples and cabbage and mix carefully.
Sprinkle top with parsley and nuts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork chop scallop
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Grease 10-inch skillet with fat. Brown chops on both sides; season with salt and pepper.
Remove chops from skillet.
Empty potato and packet of seasoning sauce mix into skillet.
Stir in pimento and amounts of water and milk called for on package. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover; simmer for 30 to 35 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4.

title: cream  puffs
directions: Add butter to boiling water in a saucepan.
Stir with plastic spoon until butter melts.
Add flour and salt all at once.
Stir fast.
Cook and stir until dough pulls away from sides of pan and forms a ball.
Take off heat and stir in eggs, 1 at a time.; Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Cut back and heat to 325°.
Cook for 25 minutes longer, then cut top of puffs and put back in cut off oven until puffs dry out.
Takes about 15 minutes.
Then fill centers just before serving, then put whipped cream on top.
Drizzle Chocolate Sauce on top.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine meal, soda, salt, cheese and eggs with milk.
Combine the rest; mix and bake in 350° oven.
Can substitute 1 1/2 teaspoons red crushed peppers for hot peppers.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns and melt cheese.
Mix melted cheese and mayonnaise. Stir in potatoes. Bake at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: hot pepperoni dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with rest of can of fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: german onion bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a food processor.
Dump in greased 10-inch cake pan and smooth out.
Saute the onion slices and place on top of the batter.
Beat egg and add sour cream and drizzle over top.
Cover with poppy seed.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage egg and cheese casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13 pan, place croutons.
Brown and drain sausage; pour evenly over croutons in the pan.
Beat eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper and pour over mixture in baking dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, uncovered, until top begins to brown.

title: crock-pot peppered steak
directions: Cut steak into strips; roll in flour and brown in skillet. Place steak, water, tomatoes, chopped onions, bell pepper and remaining ingredients in crock-pot. Cook all day. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: wet chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in large bowl (do not use electric mixer).
In pot, combine oil, oleo and cocoa; bring to boil.
Pour mixture over flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased with Pam).
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°, or until done.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls, roll in flour. Put into greased dish and cook, tightly covered, for 1 hour at 300°.

title: bread
directions: Use your favorite bread recipe. When dough has risen once, take a piece of the dough (equal to the amount of 1 loaf) and stretch it flat on a greased cookie sheet.
It will be uneven and bumpy.
Spread melted butter lightly over the dough and sprinkle lightly with coarse salt.
Do not let rise.
Put in a hot (400°) oven immediately and bake about 30 minutes or until nice and crusty.

title: lenten potato soup
directions: Cook ingredients until boiling, then make a
thickening of Coffee-mate and water and flour.
Add slowly to soup.
Cook 1 hour, then add instant potato flakes until soup is as thick as you like.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain all fruit well.
Mix all ingredients (except crusts) together.
Put in graham cracker crusts.

title: mildred's favorite rice krispie cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except oatmeal and Rice Krispies. Mix together oatmeal and Rice Krispies and fold into other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Raisins and nuts may be added.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Randomly place frozen rolls.
Mix together pudding and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over rolls.
Pour melted butter over rolls.
Sprinkle nuts.
Leave on counter uncovered overnight.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Reserve 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans and blend all other ingredients well.
Fold mixture into an airtight container and refrigerate overnight.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining nuts.

title: white christmas pie
directions: Soften gelatin and water in saucepan, then mix 1/2 cup sugar, 4 tablespoons flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 1/2 cups milk. Cook over low heat, stirring until it boils.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in softened gelatin.
Cool until partially set. Beat with rotary beaters until smooth.
Blend in 3/4 teaspoon vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon almond.
Gently fold in whipping cream, whipped stiff.

title: autumn cheese soup
directions: Place vegetables in water and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley. Heat and stir for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 5.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and oleo thoroughly.
Chill, then make into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Put in freezer, then dip in chocolate or peanut butter chips, which you melt over hot water.
May also add Rice Krispies.
Makes lots.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Saute the scallions in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add spinach and stir over low heat to dry excess water and condiments.
Taste for enough seasoning.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken in a saucepan; bring to boil.
Place chicken in a baking pan; pour mixture over chicken and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Roll in small balls, press dough with glass (glass with design if available).
Dip glass in sugar before pressing dough.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: cinnamon fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, cream butter, brown sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in flour, pecans and salt.
Shape dough into 3-inch long rolls.
Cover dough with sugar and cinnamon until well coated.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool completely before storing.

title: seafoam icing
directions: Combine whites, sugar and water in top of double boiler.
Beat well to mix.
Place over rapidly boiling water and beat constantly until mixture stands in peaks (about 7 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat until right consistency.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix to spread graham crackers and 6 tablespoons oleo on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into well-greased baking dish.
Top with additional bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake approximately 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour and all dry ingredients.
Cut shortening into flour until coarse.
Add liquid to make a soft dough.
Roll on floured surface to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and put on greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: ranch rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole in oven.
Add garlic powder.
Add rice and stir to coat with butter.
Add rest of ingredients and stir to combine.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: cheese omelet
directions: Place bread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Grate the cheeses; mix together and sprinkle on bread.
Mix together the eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle mushrooms over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked cheese and bread
directions: Spread bread with butter and cut in squares.
Cut the cheese in thin slices.
Alternate bread and cheese in baking dish, sprinkling each layer with salt and paprika.
Beat eggs; add milk and mix thoroughly.
Pour over the bread and cheese.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave in a large bowl.
Add all other ingredients into bowl and stir well until all are coated with bark. Dip out mixture with a teaspoon or size you desire onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let stand until firm.
Put in plastic bag and store in refrigerator or cool place.

title: zucchini loaf
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salad oil until creamy.
Add the grated zucchini.
Beat again, then add all remaining ingredients at the same time.
Beat until real smooth.
Grease two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Flour chicken fingers.
Heat oil in skillet.
Saute chicken. Saute pepper, onions and mushrooms.
In large pan, saute garlic in olive oil.
Add 2 cans tomatoes.
Add sauteed chicken.
Cook for about 1/2 hour, then add peppers, onions, mushrooms and wine.
Add salt and crushed red pepper to taste.
Cook 1/2 hour more.
Serve over linguine cooked al dente.
Sprinkle with Romano cheese.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine with salt, pepper, garlic and lemon juice.
Make white sauce, using margarine, flour, cream, chicken broth, salt and sherry.
Add mushrooms and chicken.
Fold in cooked spaghetti.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Place small amounts of cheese on top before baking.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Pour beans and corn into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix sour cream, water chestnuts, Cheddar cheese, chopped onion and celery soup in bowl; pour over beans and corn.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Pour melted stick of oleo over crackers.
Mix and put on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast treats
directions: Melt oleo, brown sugar, pineapple and nuts in bottom of a pie pan.
Roll
biscuits
in
mixture
of
white
sugar and cinnamon, then push down in pineapple mixture in pan.
Repeat until
all biscuits
are used, squeezing mixture up over biscuits or spoon over them;
sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake
in 425° oven until biscuits are done.
Turn out on a platter and eat while hot.

title: whippersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet; set aside. In large bowl, combine cake mix, whipped topping and egg; blend well.
Cover and chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls and dip in confectioners sugar.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: joan mondale's pumpkin bread
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Place in large bowl and add remaining ingredients in order given, mixing well.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and spoon batter into pan.
Bake about 75 to 90 minutes at 325° until bread pulls away from sides of pan and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Remove.
This bread freezes well.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on a 12-inch pizza pan.
Add pizza sauce, toppings and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Make 2 gallons of tropical punch Kool-Aid; sweeten to taste. Pour in punch bowl and add ginger ale, juice and sherbet.
Stir and serve.

title: sausage-turkey cheese balls
directions: Mix Bisquick, sausage/turkey, cheese and water.
Roll into small balls by hand.
Bake at 350°
for about 15 minutes or until brown.
Do not overbake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in large bowl; beat well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and shortening until fluffy.
Add zucchini, baking soda, baking powder, salt and flour.
Stir in pineapple, raisins and walnuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, bacon, water chestnuts, celery and grapes in a large bowl.
Set aside.
In another bowl, whisk together remaining ingredients.
Add to salad and toss to coat.
Chill until serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: party pizza appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients except biscuits.
Separate each biscuit into 3 pizza rounds.
Spread with mixture.
Put pizzas on a cookie sheet and freeze.
Remove from cookie sheet and store in plastic bags.
Bake frozen pizzas at 425° for 10 minutes.
Great for a cocktail party.
Serves 90.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat 4 eggs lightly.
Add the sugar and beat until foamy.
Add 2 cups milk and cook over medium heat until custard begins to thicken, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into ice cream churn.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into a buttered casserole dish.
Stir soft margarine into brown sugar and flour.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix in nuts.
Combine applesauce, beaten eggs, lemon juice, rind and butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir only until no dry flour is visible.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: apricot cream pie
directions: Drain juice from apricots.
Mix flour and sugar and combine with beaten egg.
Add melted butter and apricot juice.
Place apricots in pie shell.
Cut side up.
Pour custard over the apricots.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and continue baking until custard is set and crust lightly browned. Serve with whipped cream.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Cook sausage and fennel seed and drain well.
Cook beef and add oregano, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Add cheese.
After cheese has melted, add sausage and mix well. Put on rye bread.
When ready to eat, bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: butterscotch topping
directions: Boil ingredients until slightly thick; let cool.
Add 1 1/2 cups of canned milk and stir well.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and creamy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each egg is added.
Add flavorings; beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with cream.
Lightly flour walnuts; fold into mixture.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 80 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: holiday cheer
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Cool.
Cut cake in half lengthwise.
Use half the cake only.
Cut the cake into small squares. Arrange half of the squares into a glass bowl.
Layer with pudding (cook according to directions on box) on cake and half the strawberries on top of the pudding.
Repeat the layers. Chill for 4
hours.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with almonds.

title: kentucky strawberry pie
directions: Mix strawberries and 1/2 cup sugar and let stand.
Cook sugar, cornstarch and water.
Take off heat and add strawberry jello. Add the strawberries to the hot mixture and pour into baked pie crust.
Refrigerate and serve with Cool Whip.

title: fish stuffing
directions: In blender, place cottage cheese, lemon juice and seasoning. Blend until smooth.

Using either cherry tomatoes, halved or mushroom caps, green pepper wedges or celery sticks, place shrimp on vegetable and spoon cottage cheese mixture over shrimp. Refrigerate, covered, until ready to use.

title: macaroni and ham salad
directions: Cook macaroni and chill.
In large bowl place ham in small cubes, cheese, celery, onion, pickles, mayo and mustard, then stir in macaroni.
Chill and serve.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mike's batchlor meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger meat and onion soup mix.
Form into meatballs and fry in pan until done.
Drain grease.
Add two cans cream of mushroom soup.
Simmer.
To serve, throw bread in toaster and eat meatballs out of pan so not to mess up anymore dishes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Pour 1 cup of boiling water over rice for 5 minutes.
Saute onion.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Cook until broccoli is done. Pour over rice and mix together.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add kidney beans, taco mix and salt; simmer 10 minutes.
Chop onion, tomatoes and lettuce.
Toss with cheese, Italian dressing and hot sauce.
Slice and add avocado. Add hot ground beef mixture to salad.
Break tortilla chips and add to salad.
Decorate with extra tortilla chips, avocado and tomato slices.
Serve pronto!

title: citrus gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin with liquid drained from fruit (hot).
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in fruit, making sure the fruit is evenly spread.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight to congeal.

title: blueberry sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and 1 egg, beating well.
Combine flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Mix until blended. Add vanilla.
Spread into greased 9-inch spring-form pan. Sprinkle with 4 cups blueberries.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix cake and butter until crumbly. Set aside 2/3 c. Press remainder into 9x13 pan. Slice apples on top. Mix egg and sour cream together and pour over apples. Add brown sugar and cinnamon to 2/3 c. of topping and sprinkle over the top. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes. Serves 12 or more.

title: inside out chocolate cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put in well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil.
Drain off oil.
Add tomatoes.
If fresh, slice or cut into chunks.
Cut onion into chunks.
Core (remove stem and seeds) pepper.
Slice zucchini (without peeling).
Add juice from tomato if canned, otherwise, use 2 cups tomato juice and 2 cups water.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: In a mixing bowl put cake mix, oil, apricot nectar, egg yolks and lemon juice.
With mixer on low, beat 5 to 10 minutes.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread sugar evenly over bottom and arrange on top of sugar. Prepare yellow or white cake mix per directions. Pour over peaches in pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple well. In separate bowl, combine cottage cheese and dry Jell-O. Gently fold in pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip and miniature marshmallows. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: cattail wheat nut bread
directions: Sift together pollen, flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add sugar, nuts and milk.
Mix well.
Bake in 8 x 4-inch greased pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° until pie crusts are brown, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp toast(great for unexpected guests)
directions: Melt butter and cheese spread; add mayo and shrimp.
Split 6 English muffins in half.
Put the 12 halves on cookie sheet and put cheese mixture on all.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and place cookie sheet in freezer for 1 hour.
Cut each muffin half into quarters and put into a covered plastic freezer container.
When ready to serve, put desired amount of pieces on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: low country bread pudding
directions: Desserts were almost
always
made at home since stores were few and had limited supplies on the Sea Islands.
Because refrigerator was lacking
jello
was only made during the cold months when it
was
placed outside on the porch overnight for jelling.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat the butter until very fluffy.
Add sugar very slowly and beat.
Add flour very slowly and by small amounts.
Keep on beating very good.
Add potato chips and blend by hand.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cookies should be the size of a walnut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: creole red beans
directions: Cook red beans.
Brown ground chuck, onion, garlic, salt and pepper; drain grease.
Add ground meat, Ro-Tel and can tomato sauce.
Let cook about 20 minutes.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1
cup boiling water; drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Add
syrup
to gelatin mixture; mix well.
Chill until
thickened.
Fold
in
cottage
cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Pour
into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or
individual molds.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix cottage cheese and sour cream with noodles.
Brown ground beef and onion in fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, garlic salt, oregano and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: lemon-apricot special
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar together.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Spray tube pan with canola oil spray and pour in batter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool right side up for 15 minutes, then remove from pan.
Mix 1 cup confectioners sugar and juice of 1 lemon. Heat in microwave only seconds until dissolved.
Make holes in top of cake with fork and drizzle over cake while still warm.
Cake is extremely moist and just gets better every day.

title: caramel-pecan crunchies
directions: Grease pan.
Stir marshmallows, caramels, water and butter with wooden mixing spoon in saucepan over low heat until caramels and marshmallows melt.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in cereal and nuts until well coated with caramel mixture.
Press into baking pan using mixing spoon.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch squares using table knife dipped in hot water.
Store in airtight tin. Makes 5 dozen.

title: orange jelly
directions: Combine as directed for standard gelatin jelly.

title: squash or broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with dressing; divide dressing 3/4 & 1/4. Mix 3/4 of dressing with all other ingredients. Place mixture in greased casserole. Place 1/4 dressing on top. Bake uncovered 35 minutes at 350 degrees.
2 packages of frozen chopped broccoli may be used in place of squash.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans, asparagus and pimento.
Mix these together and add can of mushroom soup (undiluted).
Heat until warm all the way through in oven at 350°.
Add onion rings on top and bake about 10 minutes and serve.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn.
Combine sugar, syrup, water and vinegar.
Heat to boil.
Add cream of tartar.
Boil until it spins a thread in cold water (soft crack).
Remove from fire.
Add butter, soda and flavoring.
Stir just enough to mix and pour over freshly popped corn.
Form into balls.
Grease hands with butter to do this.

title: sharon kamerath's vanilla fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar and milk; stir.
Bring to boil; cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; let cool 2 minutes.
Add powdered sugar; beat until smooth with electric mixer (if electric mixer isn't used, powdered sugar must be sifted).
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread immediately in buttered pan.
Yields 34.

title: christmas shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Sprinkle with paprika. Serve with Fritos.

title: alabama pecan pie
directions: Put all together and mix well with rotary beater.
Put in uncooked pie shell and cook slowly about 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Put beef in bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken breasts with bacon on top.
Cover with sour cream and mushroom soup mix.
Bake 3 hours at 375° uncovered.

title: hotel roanoke spoon bread
directions: Combine water, butter, sugar and salt in medium saucepan; bring to boil.
Stir in cornmeal and boil 1 minute or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add baking powder, eggs and milk, stirring until well blended.
Pour batter into a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together peanut butter, brown sugar, white sugar, margarine and eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Roll in balls.
Put on pan and flatten with fork.
Cook at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: arroz y habichuelas(rice and red beans)
directions: Put rice in rice cooker or in pot.
In separate pot, but in beans and cook on low.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Serve hot.
Serve together or separate. Add with pork chops, steaks, or chicken.

title: carmel dip
directions: Mix together in blender or with mixer until smooth.
Serve with apples (sliced), bananas and strawberries.
Yum!

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix together pudding, pineapple, nuts, and maraschino cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into bowl and let chill about 2 hours.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Make pudding according to directions.
Add Cool Whip.
Add your favorite combinations of drained fruit such as pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges, peaches, pears, fruit cocktail, bananas, strawberries and maraschino cherries.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add vanilla and applesauce. Alternately add flour, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Bake in a well-greased and floured Bundt pan or layer pan.
Ice to your liking.
(Given to me in 1939.)

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips in saucepan with a bit of butter to keep them from sticking.
After the chips are melted, put in peanut butter and mix well.
Add oatmeal; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and let cool.

title: ice cream cake("scrumptious" - my mom's recipe)
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Mix ice cream and Cool Whip.
Spread and freeze.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in enough water to cover until tender.
Reserve broth.
Chop chicken.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread soup over chicken.
Pour broth over soup.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix flour, milk and margarine; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: leftover veggies
directions: Marinate leftover vegetables (broccoli, asparagus, carrots, beans, etc.) in Italian dressing.
Refrigerate and serve as salad or as a condiment.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Combine berries with 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice, nutmeg and margarine.
Place into a greased boiler.
