In a separate bowl, work shortening into sifted dry ingredients until mixture looks like fine cornmeal.
Mix together egg, milk and cinnamon; stir into dry ingredients using a fork.
Spread batter over berries.
Add 1 cup of water to a 3-quart saucepan.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat and when vapor appears around the edge of the double boiler, lower heat and cook 35 minutes.
Serve cobbler hot, topped with fruit, cream, whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: hot shrimp dip(microwave)
directions: Rinse, drain and finely chop shrimp.
Place cream cheese in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at Medium (50%) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until softened.
Stir in remaining ingredients except crackers.
Microwave at Medium-high (80%) for 4 to 6 minutes or until well heated, but not boiling, stirring after half the cooking time.
Transfer to serving container.
Serve warm with assorted crackers.

title: bom-boms
directions: Mix together.
Roll into little balls.
Let balls chill.
Dip into melted chocolate.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: artichoke rice salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions but omit butter. Add onions, green pepper and drained artichokes.
Mix juice of artichokes with mayonnaise and curry powder.
Add to rice mixture. Add almonds and raisins.

title: chicken stew and dumplings
directions: Wash chicken and cut as for frying.
Discard any large gobs of fat; remove all of skin.
Dry well on paper towels.

title: black-eyed pea soup
directions: Sort and rinse peas.
In large skillet, saute onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add these both to a large pot. Cover with water.
Add bay leaf, thyme and salt; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until peas are tender.
Add tomatoes and meats.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8 (high fiber).

title: serbian cabbage
directions: Put cabbage in 4-quart dish.
Pour milk on.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more, until bread crumbs are lightly browned and cabbage is tender.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, pumpkin and eggs.
Mix together flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add this to creamed mixture, then add vanilla.
If desired, add raisins, nuts, coconut or chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes a large batch.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until lightly brown.
Add to tuna and mushroom soup.
Add pepper.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes. May be topped with cornstarch and milk.
Season to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Measure flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together into a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is like meal.
Add milk to egg.
Add liquid ingredients to flour mixture.
Stir only until flour is moistened.
Blend in blueberries lightly.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: angel wings (polish)(chrusciki)
directions: Add salt to egg yolks and beat until thick and lemon colored. Add sour cream with vanilla flavoring alternately with flour and mixing well after each addition.
Knead on floured board until the dough blisters.
Cut in half and roll each half very thin.
Now, cut into strips about 4 inches long. Make 2 inch slits lengthwise through center and pull one end through, making angel wing.
Fry in hot oil until lightly browned. Drain on paper towel and sprinkle generously with powdered sugar.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Stir in sugar, salt, oleo and flour. Beat well.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled (about 1 hour).
Punch dough down and roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in diamonds about 2 1/2-inches long.
Dip each piece in melted oleo and arrange in layers in a tube pan.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Tear off pieces instead of cutting.

title: fried cheese meltaways
directions: Heat oil (2 inches deep) to 375°.
Beat 1 cup Bisquick, milk and egg until smooth.
Coat cheese cubes lightly with Bisquick. Insert a round toothpick in each cheese cube; dip into batter, covering cheese completely.
Fry several cubes at a time, turning carefully, until golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: gladys beach's green stuff dessert
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburg in olive oil. Add onions and green pepper. Also seasonings (to taste). Add puree, sauce and water. Simmer for 3 to 4 hours.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook meat until well done in a large pot with plenty of water. When done, add vegetables and tomato juice.
For fat-free soup, leave off meat and use 3 beef bouillon cubes.
Cook until done, approximately an hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil onion, celery and potatoes until tender.
Save water. (Mash potatoes if you want.)
Add salt, butter and canned milk. Add instant potatoes to thicken.

title: mom's fruit salad
directions: Chop apple and cheese in a bowl. In a saucepan, mix egg, flour, sugar and pineapple juice, stirring after each addition. Cook over medium heat until thick. Pour over apple and cheese. Spread pineapple over salad and place cherries in centers of pineapple. Sprinkle with nuts. (Some of the pineapple, cherries and nuts may be mixed in the salad.)

title: quick saucy chicken stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium-high heat. Stir-fry vegetables 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender. Remove.
Add remaining oil to skillet.
Stir-fry chicken 4 minutes or until tender.
Return vegetables.
Remove from heat.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Carnation milk, pudding, Cool Whip and 3 cups milk on medium speed until well blended.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas and 1/2 of filling.
Repeat layers and refrigerate overnight. Keep refrigerated until all is used.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Combine other ingredients; pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350°.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Cook noodles in unsalted water and drain.
Mix with soup, milk, tuna, cheese and onion.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with broken potato chips or grated cheese.
Bake in hot oven at 425° until bubbly hot, about 15 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: barley vegetable soup
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Put all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 hour, or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaves.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix potatoes with mixer; then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into an 11 x 15-inch greased pan.

title: red salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in 1 cup hot water.
Add jello and other cup of hot water.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Place bread pieces in pan. Sprinkle browned and drained sausage over bread.
Add grated cheese, then add beaten eggs to milk, onion and pepper.
Pour over mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until brown on top.
Let set 15 minutes before cutting. Serves 9.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Make a fourth layer with Cool Whip. Top with grated Hershey's candy bar. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows in boiling water; add cold water.
Stir in pineapple and peaches.
Chill.

title: egg souffle casserole
directions: Combine sausage, bread and Cheddar cheese.
Put into flat 10 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs, salt, milk and mustard.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Cover and chill overnight (optional). Combine mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over casserole and bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
During last 20 to 30 minutes, remove cover so casserole can brown slightly.

title: easy microwave chinese style chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken breast in microwave on High for 5 minutes in a covered dish.

title: goody bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking sheet. Beat together the margarine, sugar and corn syrup in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into baking sheet.
Press firmly into pan with moist fingers.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.
When cool, refrigerate one hour before cutting.
Cut into 2-inch bars.

title: "chicken and dressing casserole"
directions: Place last 6 ingredients in blender.
Add soup and mix well. Layer 1/2 of dressing mix in casserole.
Add cut chicken and other half of dressing mix.
Pour liquids over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Can be frozen before or after cooking. (I add a little sage.)

title: busy day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep baking pan.
Pour fruit in.
In small bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Pour in milk and stir well.
Pour batter over top of fruit. Bake 45 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: christmas rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in powdered sugar and store in tin.
Makes about 48 balls.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water 25 to 30 minutes.
Drain.
Slice potatoes.
In a skillet cook ham, onion, green pepper and celery in oleo until tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in sour cream, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil. Combine sour cream mixture and potatoes.
Serve at once.
Serves 10.

title: sour cream fudge torte cake
directions: Blend devil's food cake mix, eggs, water and oil.
Put in three layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool cake in pans before frosting.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all these ingredients and set aside.
Brown 1 pound of ground meat in skillet and drain.
Grate 1/2 pound mild Cheddar cheese, 3 or 4 jalapeno peppers and 1 large onion (all finely chopped).
In large well-greased pan, pour half of cornbread mix, then your ground meat, then your cheese, onion and peppers.
Last, add your remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: glazed corned beef
directions: Cover beef with water in large Dutch oven.
Add peppercorns, onion, cloves
and	celery.
Simmer
about	5
hours or until almost tender;
add
water,
if
needed.
Remove brisket from water.
Place
in	baking	pan.
Combine
brown
sugar, mustard, horseradish,
catsup, vinegar and butter in saucepan. Stir over medium
heat
until
blended and bubbly.
Spoon some sauce over meat.
Bake at 350° or until meat is tender; baste several times with remaining sauce.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Combine flour, half the nuts and melted butter; mix well. Spread into a 9-inch square pan and bake 15 minutes at 375°. Chill. Beat cream cheese with powdered sugar until smooth. Add 1 cup of Cool Whip and stir until blended.
Spread over chilled crust. Mix the pudding and milk according to package directions; spread over cheese layer. Top with rest of Cool Whip and sprinkle with remaining nuts. Chill for several hours.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, beaten egg yolks, water, coconut, salt and butter, in that order.
Cook in an uncooked pie shell until done.
Top with beaten egg whites.
Brown top at 350°.

title: friendship sourdough bread(potato feed)
directions: Using a wooden spoon in a small bowl, mix ingredients real well, then pour into starter.
Let stand out of refrigerator 8 to 12 hours with top on very loosely. Soon you will see it start to bubble. After 8 to 12 hours, take 1 cup starter out to make your bread.
Return the rest to the refrigerator and in 3 to 4 days, feed starter again.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine milk, eggs, salt and flour.
Heat oil to 400°.
Fill funnel with batter, holding finger over opening.
Hold funnel over oil and allow batter to flow, making coils and swirls, frying on each side for 1 to 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or serve with jelly.
Serve while hot.

title: bacon appetizers
directions: Mix together enough spread for 24 Melba toasts.
Cover each toast, bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Blend oleo, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix in oatmeal, corn flakes, chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Use ice cream scoop and mold cookies, placing only 4 cookies at a time on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: opera fudge
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Chill overnight.
Roll into balls and put in freezer an hour before coating with chocolate.
Peanut butter may be added to taste or coconut.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Add all ingredients in large bowl; mix by hand.
Do not use mixer.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: soft pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, pumpkin, shortening and orange peel.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: fruit pizza dessert
directions: SOFTEN COOKIE DOUGH AND SPREAD IN PIZZA PAN. Bake according to directions until golden brown. Cool.

title: beef goulash
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch cubes.
Brown in large pan in oil.
Mix tomato paste, onion soup mix and water together.
Pour in pan with meat.
Cover and let simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly the butter, shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and the eggs.
Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls. Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Roll balls in mixture. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Immediately remove from baking sheet. Yields about 6 dozen cookies.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Cut sausage in pieces about 1 1/2-inches each.
Fry in vegetable oil 20 to 25 minutes and set aside.
Fry peppers in oil until tender. Add salt, pepper and Italian seasoning. Add peppers and sausage and simmer about 15 minutes. Eat with Italian bread!

title: chicken with cranberry sauce
directions: Combine cranberry sauce, salad dressing and soup and mix well. Marinate chicken in this mixture overnight or 8 hours.
Place chicken with sauce in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: brisket
directions: Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours (until tender).
Cool; refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin.
Reheat before serving (juice good with noodles or gravy).

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, saute onion, celery and broccoli in oleo for 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth.
Place rice in greased 8-inch pan.
Pour cheese mixture over.
Do not stir.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 30 minutes. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pork ribs
directions: One package of ribs is 4 or 5 ribs; will feed 2 people.
Allow extra for snacking.

title: hobo vegetables
directions: Cut 6 pieces heavy aluminum foil, 18 x 12-inch size.
Divide vegetables among foil, placing in center (3 vegetables, potatoes, onions and carrots).
In small bowl, put margarine, garlic, salt and pepper.
Brush this mixture over vegetables in each foil pocket, using it all.
Bring up long sides of foil, leaving space for steam.
Seal tightly with a double fold.
Fold short ends to seal.
Grill packets on uncovered grill directly over medium coals 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Turn over once. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Remove seed from pepper.
Process vinegar with peppers in blender.
Put in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add sugar.
Bring to boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add liquid pectin. Bring back to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Wipe jar rims and adjust lids.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes five 8 ounce jars.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Wash seeds in cold water.
Spread them on paper towels to dry, about 2 hours.
Next, toss them with melted butter and salt.
Then place a single layer of seeds in a baking pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes until lightly toasted.
Stir once.
Let cool.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cook the milk, cornstarch and salt until thick, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cool.
Beat butter with sugar.
Add vanilla.
When blended, add cooled mixture gradually.

title: carrots and onions with cream
directions: Split carrots into narrow strips.
Slice onion very thin. Boil carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Saute onions in margarine and add cream or evaporated milk.
Bring to the boil stage but do not let cream boil.
Add carrots; serve warm.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken in salsa, juice and garlic for 1 to 8 hours. Saute onions and peppers until limp.
Add chicken and marinade and cook down to sauce.
Roll into heated corn tortilla shells.
Top with sour cream and more salsa.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine in a large bowl the oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In a separate bowl, combine milk, vanilla pudding and Cool Whip.
Blend mixtures together.
In a serving container, begin with cookie layer of cream cheese mixture and end with cookies.

title: curry dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend in milk to desired consistency. Add curry to taste.
Place in bowl and cover with chutney (Major Grey's or other).
Dip with crisp gingersnaps.
It really is wonderful.

title: deep dish sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes; cool slightly.
Place in mixing bowl; beat until smooth.
Stir in butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix in spices, vanilla, salt and milk.
Pour in shells.
Bake at 375° for 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: almond chicken with wild rice
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pour wild rice mix, soup, water and 1/2 of the almonds.
Arrange chicken breasts on the bed of rice. Sprinkle remaining almonds over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat
eggs.
Combine
with
other
ingredients	(except cracker crumbs and	butter). Pour into buttered casserole; dot with butter. Sprinkle with	cracker
crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean. Serves 6.

title: barbecued spiced ham
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Add flour, black pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and water.
Cook and stir until smooth. Add ham.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in blender.
Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Now combine the creamy mixture with pudding mixture.
Layer cookies and cream mixture in a new, clean 8-inch flower pot, starting and ending with cookies.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving, if possible.
Serve with a new spade.
Insert foil wrapped artificial silk flower in dessert so as to look like flower arrangement.

title: holiday bread roll
directions: Cream shortening and both sugars.
Add eggs; blend well.
Add water and sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Add pumpkin or sweet potatoes, raisins and nuts.
Grease and flour three 1-pound empty coffee cans.
Place even amounts of mixture in all 3 cans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from cans.
When completely cool, slice in rounds.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Layer cheeses and green chilies in ungreased 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine next four ingredients and pour over cheese and chilies.
Sprinkle remaining spices over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or 45 minutes.
Slice in 1-inch squares.
Serve hot.

title: crab stew
directions: Mix
together.	Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.

title: bran breakfast
directions: Combine all ingredients and soak 10 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix dressing with milk and mayonnaise.
Spread over top of salad and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out cookie dough; place on pizza pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Do not overbake.
Let stand until cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown chili meat until dark gray.
Add garlic, black pepper, Chili Quick and flour.
Pour enough water over the mixture to cover meat.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, butter and graham cracker crumbs. Form into balls about the size of a walnut or a little smaller. Chill in the refrigerator an hour or overnight. Melt 1/2 package of chocolate candy coating, checking and stirring often and dip peanut butter balls to coat.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ground (chuck) or hamburger with soup and sliced potatoes and onions.
Pour into glass baking dish.
(Do not cook hamburger before mixing.)
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Meat could be a little pink looking but it still will be done, use your own judgment.

title: mom's cottage cheese pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and nutmeg and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat thoroughly with electric mixer. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle crumbs over pie.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; work in flour, oats and pecans. Press on lightly oiled pan (cookie sheet if a double batch). Prick with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cream the cheese, vanilla and sugar in small bowl.
Blend well.
Spread over crust and top with fruit slices of choice.

title: tomato and chili salsa
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Use at once or chill.
Store in refrigerator up to 3 days.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix Bisquick and shortening until crumbly.
Roll out thinner than for biscuits.
Put frozen or fresh blueberries in an 8-inch baking dish.
Put sugar, lemon juice and oleo (cut) and 1/2 cup of water in dish.
Cover with crust.
Sprinkle a tablespoon of sugar on top.
Punch holes so steam can come out while baking.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: batter for fried shrimp or onion rings
directions: Sift dry
ingredients;	add
water
and oil; beat until smooth.
Fold in egg
white
just before frying.
Coat fantail shrimp or onion rings and fry in deep fat until brown.

title: scones
directions: Take the bread out of cabinet.
Take the jelly and put it on the bread.
Then put the peanut butter on, then fold the bread over and eat it.

title: dump salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple.
Dump drained fruit into a bowl.
Add sliced bananas.
Add cherry pie filling.
Stir to mix.
Be sure bananas are under the surface of mixture. Refrigerate for 2 or 3 hours.
May be kept overnight without a problem.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Combine squash, milk, beaten egg yolks, sugar and seasonings. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour mixture into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° and bake until center of pie is set, about 45 minutes.
Serve pie with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: sourdough muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together with an electric mixer.
Put into muffins and let stand for 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: marinated brussels sprouts
directions: Place pickling spices (2 tablespoons) and dash of fresh ground pepper in metal tea ball.
Place in center of bowl with lid to marinate Brussels sprouts.

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix together; water, tea and sugar.
Add orange juice, lemonade and vodka.
Freeze until slushy, stir every once in a while.
Serve a 1/2 glass of slush with a half glass of pop.

title: kelly's cucumber sandwiches
directions: Halve cucumber and scrape out seeds, then grate.
Squeeze out water.
Mix together with mayonnaise and garlic salt.
Spread on bread and cut into small sandwiches.

title: quick and easy chocolate cake
directions: In mixing bowl put flour, sugar and salt.
In saucepan put oleo oil, water and cocoa.
Let mixture come to a boil and pour over mixture in bowl.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mrs. era ray's pie shells
directions: Cut first 3 ingredients together.
Mix water, vinegar and egg together and add to flour mixture.
Mix together well and roll out.
This will keep in refrigerator several seeks.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
Mix eggs, milk and 1/2 cup of cheese together; add to macaroni.
Cook in microwave for 7 minutes on High with cover.
Add remaining cheese; cook for 3 minutes on High, uncovered.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Great for birthday parties.

title: apple crisp
directions: In bowl, mix apples, sugar and lemon juice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, brown sugar and butter.
Pour onto apple mixture.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Spread mixture of melted margarine and cracker crumbs in large cake pan.
Beat until fluffy the sugar, eggs and margarine and spread on top of first layer.
Add pineapple, then add sliced bananas and Cool Whip.
Spread pecans over top.
Add cherries. Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Tear 3 cans of biscuits into fourths; shake in a sack (a few at a time) with 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Boil margarine and brown sugar for one minute.
Layer biscuits in well-greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Layer again. Sprinkle with pecans.
Pour boiled mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook peanuts, sugar, Karo syrup and water in heavy pan until peanuts turn light brown (about 15 minutes).
Take off burner. Stir in soda, salt and butter.
Pour on greased cookie sheet. Spread as thin as possible and cool.

title: dreamy apricot salad
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and water in a small saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar and gelatin.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit; set aside to cool.
Combine condensed milk and cream cheese, beating until smooth; stir in gelatin mixture, then nuts.
Pour into a 9-cup mold and chill until firm.
Yields about 20 servings.

title: spinach with bacon
directions: Cook and stir bacon and onion in a 10-inch skillet until bacon is crisp.
Add about half of spinach and salt.
Cook over medium heat, about 2 minutes.
Add remaining spinach.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until spinach is tender, about 3 to 10 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: May add 1/4 cup sweet salad cubes, if you like, and top as you like.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail (do not drain), raisins, coconut, nuts, miniature marshmallows, bananas and cut up apples. Add mayonnaise.

title: chicken croissants
directions: Mix together cream cheese, melted margarine, chicken, chives, salt and pepper.
Use this as filling between two crescent rolls. Pinch edge together to seal.
Brush melted butter and crushed croutons on top before baking.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add egg and fruit cocktail.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: death by chocolate(serves 15)
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions and bake in a 9 x 13-inch rectangle pan.
Cool cake in pan.
When cool, break cake up with a fork.
Pour coffee evenly over cake pieces.
Refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Prepare mousse as per directions on box.

title: charoset
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Be sure apples are finely chopped, but do not use food processor as it makes apples mushy. Makes 10 heaping tablespoons.

title: colleen mundt's friendship pie
directions: *OK to substitute 2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice for these 3 spices.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut 12 refrigerator biscuits into thirds (to make 36 pieces).
Roll each piece into a ball.
Mix together in small bowl 4 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Roll the dough balls in the cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Set aside.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in pineapple.
Combine flour and soda.
Stir into mixture.
Bake in pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Put on Cool Whip topping before you serve it.

title: smoked turkey fettucini
directions: Cook noodles.
Chop turkey into cubes.
Melt butter or margarine in medium saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk and broth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper, turkey and mushrooms.
Continue heating until turkey is hot.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Stir and add flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat until smooth.
This should be thin enough to run through a small funnel.
Drop from funnel into hot, deep fat, about 375°, and turn.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Coat a shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with vegetable oil spray.
Stir flour into nonfat milk until it dissolves.
Spray frying pan with vegetable spray and saute onion.
Blend in cheese.
When cheese has melted, add broccoli. Pour into casserole dish.
Add egg whites and mix gently.
Cut sheets of phyllo dough in half.
Top casserole mixture, alternating one piece of dough with one spray of vegetable oil to make 6 layers.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: cola burgers
directions: In a bowl, combine the egg, 1/4 cup cola, cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons salad dressing, Parmesan cheese and salt.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into six 3/4 inch thick patties (the mixture will be moist).
In a bowl, combine the remaining cola and salad dressing; set aside.
Grill patties, uncovered, over medium hot heat for 3 minutes on each side.
Brush with cola mixture.
Grill 8 to 10 minutes longer or until juices run clear, basting and turning occasionally.
Serve on buns.
(Diet cola is not recommended for this recipe.)

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook broccoli for 3 minutes.
Salt broccoli and drain water off of broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry coconut cake(best made the day before)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Make cake as package directs.
Turn into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake on lowest shelf of oven, 30 to 40 minutes.
Invert pan and cool cake 1 1/2 hours.
Meanwhile make strawberry filling.
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and sifted cornstarch; stir to mix well.
Add strawberries with the liquid.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from the heat. Turn filling into medium bowl.
Place a sheet of waxed paper directly into the strawberry surface.
Refrigerate until well chilled, approximately 2 hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place sliced apples on the bottom of an 8 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and crumble over top of the apples.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes (when apples are done).
Tastes great with ice cream or milk.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Pound chicken until it is nice and flat.
Cut chicken into strips.
Cover bottom of inside frying pan with 1/4 inch cooking oil.
Cut lemons into fourths.
Cut onions into fine strips. Saute lemons and onion over medium heat.
When light brown in color, add chicken.
Cook over medium to low heat until chicken starts to brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice with a slice of lemon as garnish.

title: special k crumb no-bake bar cookies
directions: In saucepan, bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal and mix until coated.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not press down.
Melt chocolate (double boiler or microwave) and frost.
Cut into bars. Yield:
3 dozen cookies.

title: funnel cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Mix both mixtures together and cook in hot oil.
For one, use about 1/2 cup of batter.
Pour in a thin stream into hot oil.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat with medium onion; drain excess grease.
Add all ingredients, except chips.
Simmer about 25 minutes.
Serve with taco chips or corn bread.
Real good with jalapeno corn bread.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water for about 3 minutes, then plunge into cold water.
Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice and anchovy paste.
Mix drained broccoli flowerets, sliced onions (separated into rings) and mushrooms.
Toss with mayonnaise mixture.
Add pepper to taste.

title: sweet sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Set aside.
Make salad dressing.

title: spiced grapefruit upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Finely grate about 1/2 grapefruit peel; reserve.
Peel and cut grapefruit into 6 cartwheels and drain well.

title: swiss onion pie
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Add onion; cook until transparent.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add salt; stir in cream.
Pour into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with grated cheese; dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes, or until firm (test with knife as you would for baked custard).
Crumble bacon over baked pie.

title: basic bread
directions: Dissolve yeast. Add milk, sugar, salt, shortening and half the flour.
Mix until smooth.
Mix in rest of the flour until dough is easy to handle. Knead on floured surface until smooth, 10 minutes should do it.
Put in a greased bowl. Cover with dish towel and let it rise about 1 hour, until double.

title: cherry salad
directions: Slice bananas and dip in lemon juice.
Combine all ingredients and chill several hours before serving.
Salad is better if made the day before serving.

title: pralines
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, soda, buttermilk, salt and butter.
Cook over high heat for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly until candy reaches soft ball stage, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add pecans.
Beat until light and creamy.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper and cool.

title: no bake noodle lasagna
directions: Brown and drain the hamburger and mix with the Ragu.
Put half in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread lasagna noodles to cover without overlapping.
Spread cottage cheese, 1 1/2 cups of Mozzarella cheese and as much Parmesan cheese as you want.
Do another layer of noodles the same.
Finish with rest of meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese and at least 1 cup Parmesan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° and let stand 15 minutes after baking.

title: abby's cheesecake
directions: Mix well. Pour ingredients into spring-form pan (the crust is as yet unbaked) and bake in preheated oven at 350° for approximately 50 minutes. Do not turn off oven. Remove cheesecake and top with 1 pint commercial sour cream and return to oven for another 5 minutes. Let cake cool. Top with 1 can (21 ounces) prepared pie filling or topping. (Take your choice of blueberries, cherry or strawberry.) Chill overnight.

title: swiss vegetables medley
directions: Combine
vegetables, soup, 1/2 of shredded cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 of French fried onions.
Pour into
a
1 quart
casserole dish.
Bake covered 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with
remaining cheese and fried onions.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: 1948 cocoa fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Stir in milk and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Continue boiling until soft ball (236° on a candy thermometer) is formed when small amount is dropped from spoon into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Allow to stand until fairly cool, then beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: overnight buns
directions: Start about 4 p.m.
Makes 75 to 90 hamburger buns.

title: chicken with julienne vegetables(microwave)
directions: You will need 4 microwave paper towels.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and butter until melted (2 minutes). Stir.
Add sugar; mix in eggs and vanilla, then add flour and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: dried beef ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with dried beef.
Add olive juice to ease mixing.
Dice olives and mix in.
Garnish with olives after cheese spread is shaped into ball.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until dissolved; bring to boiling, stirring often.
Cook without stirring to 248° or until a little dropped in a cup of cold water forms a firm ball.
While candy is cooking, beat egg white and cream of tartar stiff but not dry.
Use a large mixer bowl.
While beating constantly, pour syrup in a fine stream over beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and continue to beat until candy forms a peak and loses its gloss.
Stir in chopped nuts by hand. Drop onto wax paper.
Make the size you want.
I use a heaping tablespoon.
Push off spoon with spatula or knife.
Use cherries for garnish.

title: herbed fish bake
directions: Place fillets in greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in seasonings; cook 1 minute.
Spread over fish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pasta and broccoli and olive oil
directions: Cook the rotelle according to package, 8 to 10 minutes in boiling water. Dice the garlic cloves. Saute in the oil 5 to 8 minutes.
Add to drained rotelle. Season with salt, pepper and grated cheese. Save some of the pasta water. If mixed pasta is dry after seasoning, add water, one tablespoon at a time.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Soften butter or margarine and blend in sugar. Add beaten eggs, vanilla and lemon juice. Mix well. Stir in coconut and pour into unbaked deep-dish pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Top will be light brown when done.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Freeze overnight.
When serving, fill each glass about 2/3 full with slush and add 7-Up.

title: fluffy banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk with a mixer until thickened.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix.
Repeat layers.
Use a 9-inch square pan or a little larger.
You may add 1/8 teaspoon almond extract or 1/8 teaspoon banana extract.

title: nilla banana pudding
directions: Layer wafers and sliced bananas in bottom of a large bowl. Mix pudding and milk well.
Add Cool Whip and blend together. Pour over bananas.
Let chill.
Store in refrigerator.

title: veal or chicken piccata
directions: Cut veal or chicken into serving size pieces.
Coat each piece with flour.
Heat butter in a skillet.
Add meat and cook over fairly high heat until lightly brown on both sides.
If not enough room in skillet for all the meat, saute and remove until all meat is cooked.
Return all to pan.
Squeeze half of the lemon over meat.
Add the wine and stir gently.
Cook about 1 minute. Remove to warm platter and garnish with lemon slices and parsley.

title: banana cherry nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Stir in bananas and lemon juice. Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts and cherries. Pour in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground chuck, bacon, and chopped onions until done.
Add soup, sugar and beans and pour into a 9x13 pan.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serves 8-12.

title: venison roast
directions: Place roast on a large piece of heavy aluminum foil.
Sprinkle soup over roast.
Bring edges of foil together so that it is sealed tightly.
Place in shallow baking dish and bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Thicken juice for gravy, if desired.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Saute onions in butter.
Blend in flour, garlic salt and pepper.
Stir in milk, broth and water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sauce is thick.
Fold in chicken and Veg-All.
Pour in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with canned biscuits.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Make the day before or very early on the day of serving. Serve with raw carrots, celery, radishes, cauliflower, zucchini, cucumbers, etc.
A favorite always.

title: oven-baked chops
directions: Mix bread crumbs and soup mix.
Dip chops in egg. Cover chops with mixture.
Dab butter on chops.
Place on ungreased pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: herb garlic bread
directions: Mix all herbs together. Pound them in a mortar and pestle if you have one.

Add 1/2 cup margarine and blend all together. Slice a loaf of French bread and spread herb mixture between slices. Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until margarine has melted into the bread.

title: centennial holiday vegetable salad
directions: Mix all but last three ingredients 24 hours before serving. Chill. Just before serving, add remaining three ingredients. Serves 100.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix and press cookies and butter into pie pan.
Chill for 1 hour in freezer.
Pour ice cream into the shell and put into the freezer until it hardens.
Add fudge and whipped toppings.

title: broccoli parmesan cheese bake
directions: Partially steam cook broccoli spears.
Beat egg whites; add mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Then whip to a stiff consistency.

title: scottish eggs supreme
directions: Mix together the ground pork, fennel seed, cayenne, red pepper, sage, salt and pepper. Divide into 8 equal balls. Form a small patty in your hand with the first ball. Place a hard-boiled egg in the center of the patty and mold the patty to form a thin layer around the entire egg. Repeat for the remaining eggs. Chill for a minimum of 20 minutes. Put the 3 beaten eggs in a bowl and the breadcrumbs in a separate bowl. Dip each chilled, sausage-coated egg into the breadcrumbs; coat thoroughly. Next, dip it into the eggs, then back into the breadcrumbs again. Repeat for the remaining eggs. Chill for a minimum of 15 minutes.

title: lime cheesecake
directions: Put light pie filling on top (optional).

title: muffin surprise
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease or line 12 muffin cups.
Mix dry ingredients with a wooden spoon.
Beat egg.
Add milk and oil until well mixed.
Pour milk mixture over flour mixture; stir until flour is wet.
Batter should be lumpy.
Spoon half batter into muffin pans until 1/3 full.
Place a teaspoonful of jelly on the batter in each cup.
Fill muffin cups with remaining batter. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Remove label and place unopened can in a pot of water deep enough to completely cover the can.
Bring water to a boil; keep it at a slow boil for 4 hours.
Additional water may be needed to keep the can totally covered with water.
At the end of 4 hours, remove the can and cool, then open the can and enjoy a yummy caramel sauce dip.

title: diamond restaurant baked beans
directions: For each pound of baked beans do the following:
fry bacon crisp. Drain. Saute onion in grease until tender. Add bacon, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and ketchup. Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk.
Beat for 1 minute.
Add vanilla ice cream.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour mixture into 2 well greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in small amount of salted water until tender. Saute onions in margarine.
Stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute stirring constantly.
Blend in milk, salt, pepper and cauliflower. Cook and stir until thickened.
Garnish with paprika and chopped parsley.
For satin-smooth soup, use blender.
Makes 8 (3/4 cup) servings.
Broccoli or asparagus may be substituted for cauliflower.

title: smothered quail
directions: Put butter in heavy skillet and brown quail, (lightly flour quail).
Remove quail to baking dish.
Add flour to butter in skillet and stir well.
Slowly add chicken broth and sherry. Blend well and pour over quail.
Cover baking dish and bake at 350° until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: goat cheese spread
directions: Coat a 9-inch spring-form pan with cooking spray; set aside. Combine cheeses; beat at medium-high speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Add eggs, egg yolk and pesto sauce.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely on a wire rack.

title: pork chops for two dinner
directions: In a large skillet heat oil on high.
Brown chops on both sides; set aside.
Toss cabbage and brown sugar.
Place in 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with potatoes and beans.
Put chops on top.
Sprinkle pepper on top.
Pour apple juice over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Put on top.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: concord grape conserve
directions: Separate skins from
grapes.
Cook pulp until seeds are loosened.
Put through strainer.
Combine skins, pulp, chopped oranges and raisins
(put
oranges
and
raisins
through food chopper or food processor).
Add
sugar.
Cook 1 hour or until thick.
Add nuts.
Put in sterile jars and seal with wax.

title: hot cabbage
directions: Fry bacon and set aside. Slice cabbage and add to bacon drippings. Add vinegar and Ro-tel tomatoes. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and cook down. Sprinkle bacon on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze all the water out.
Dice chestnuts and onion; mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or French bread.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/8-inch diagonal pieces.
Salt and pepper; brown in oil.
Add onion, garlic, green pepper, celery and bouillon.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce; add to mixture.
Cook until juice thickens.
Serve with hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion.
Cook and stir.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook with onion 2 minutes.
Add water and bring to boil. Cook 10 minutes.
Remove half of potatoes and mash (blender).
Add milk.
Return to saucepan.
Add carrots, zucchini and green pepper. Simmer.
Stir in salt, pepper and parsley.
Cook until all vegetables are tender.

title: avocado dip
directions: Add avocado to cream cheese and blend until smooth.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, onion and chilies.
Blend well. Serve with cut up veggies or chips.

title: dairy special casserole
directions: Stir in browned ground beef in buttered skillet.
Stir in tomato sauce; remove from heat. Boil noodles in salted water 10 minutes; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper.
Spread half the noodles in buttered 2 quart casserole.

title: easy pan cake
directions: Butter large sheet pan.
Place pineapple on bottom of pan. Next, place blueberries.
Sprinkle sugar on top of blueberries. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of blueberries and sugar.
Pour melted margarine on cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top. Bake according to directions on cake mix box.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the Cool Whip, powdered sugar, cream cheese and peanut butter all together.
Put in graham cracker crust. Grate the Hershey bar and sprinkle on top.

title: italian tortellini salad
directions: Thaw frozen vegetables.
Drain.
Cut Provolone or Mozzarella cheese into 1/2-inch cubes.
Drain olives.

title: very green dressing
directions: Whip all ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites, sugar and salt until it holds peaks; then fold in vanilla, chocolate chips and pecans. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
When you put cookies in oven, turn heat off.
Forget until morning or at least 5 hours.

title: smothered okra
directions: Saute onions and tomatoes together in oil, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Add okra, stir well and cook on medium heat in a partially covered pot, about 45 minutes or until okra is no longer slimy.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tomato sauce dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium-low heat for a few minutes.
Cool or serve warm if desired.

title: jiffy hamburger soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add next four ingredients and simmer covered 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Skim off fat.
Serves 8.
Add any leftover vegetables.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Add cocoa, shortening and butter and melt over hot water. Combine sugar and syrup in saucepan. Bring to a quick boil for 2 minutes. Add cocoa mixture. Pour slowly over eggs, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and pecans; mix well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool. Top with whipped cream.

title: pastry dough
directions: Mix butter and flour, add sour cream.
Wrap dough in wax paper or Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into squares.
Place 1 tablespoon pie filling.
Press edges together.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° until golden brown.
Glaze with powdered sugar and water mixture.

title: turtles
directions: Place nuts in candy paper.
Cook milk and syrup over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it forms a medium ball.
Spoon over nuts.
Melt chocolate and spoon over caramel.
Let set.
Can be stored in refrigerator.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco seasoning until blended.
Mix in additional ingredients and moisten with Western dressing.
Mix in taco chips just before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients, then add 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 1/2 cup raisins.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup milk; let stand 1 minute. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tiny bubbles form around edge and gelatin completely dissolves. Pour hot mixture into blender. Add chocolate chips. Cover and blend until chocolate melts. Add egg, ice, sugar, almond extract, 1/2 cup whipping cream and remaining 3/4 cup milk. Blend until smooth.
Pour into six 6 ounce parfait glasses. Chill in freezer 15 minutes. Whip remaining 1/2 cup whipping cream and spoon a dollop on each serving of mousse.

title: pork chop apple skillet
directions: Brown pork chops in a large skillet over medium heat, about
3 minutes on each side.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Allow enough time before chicken is done to cook rice as package directs.
Put rice on plate; spoon chicken and soup mixture over and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix broth with dressing.
Mix together the remaining ingredients except cheese.
Layer in oblong pan in order:
dressing, chicken, mixed ingredients.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage and ground beef
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage and drain. Brown ground chuck with onion, salt and pepper (if desired).
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: karen's stroganoff
directions: Brown beef. Stir in soups and garlic.
Simmer 20 minutes. Serve over noodles. Serves 4 to 6.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon, beef and onion until lightly brown.
Drain if there is excessive grease.
Stir in salt, ketchup, mustard and vinegar.
Add sugar and beans; mix well.
Pour into 3 quart casserole dish, cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter until well blended.
Add both kinds of sugar.
Beat eggs slightly and add to sugar and butter mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamy mixture. Add more flour if dough is not stiff enough.
Add vanilla.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and cornstarch.
Cook, stirring, until thick and clear; remove from heat.
Add strawberry gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Pour over sliced berries in pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Cover with whipped cream before serving.

title: oven pancake popover
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
When hot, put 1 tablespoon of butter in iron skillet to melt.
Swirl melted butter in skillet to coat. Add batter.
Bake 20 minutes or until high and light brown. Garnish with powdered sugar or plain ole butter and syrup.
Serve with fried apples and sausages.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: crispy chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: In shallow dish, dip chicken into egg; coat with bread crumbs. In skillet over medium-low heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 15 minutes or until browned on both sides and no longer pink. Remove; keep warm.
Pour off fat.
In skillet over low heat, combine soup, milk and water.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over chicken with parslied rice.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes if desired.

title: olivita crostini
directions: In medium bowl,
stir together black and green olives, Parmesan cheese, butter, olive oil and garlic until well blended. Stir in Monterey Jack cheese and parsley.

title: carrot and zucchini muffins
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, wheat germ, soda, cinnamon and salt. Beat egg; stir in buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Stir mixture with vegetables, raisins and nuts into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin pan cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes a little better than 2 dozen muffins.

title: taco salad
directions: Stir together all ingredients except nacho chips.
Just before serving add nacho chips and toss again.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Make into balls and brown. Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Beat the eggs; add all the other ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Fix Jell-O according to package directions.
While warm, dissolve cranberry sauce in it; chill.
When partially set, fold in other ingredients.
Great for holiday season.

title: shrimp creole pronto
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add onion, celery, bell peppers and garlic; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients except rice; cook 2 to 3 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Serve over hot cooked rice or noodles.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Mix all ingredients; fill each shell with mixture and line up in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with Cheddar cheese and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Muy Buno!!!

title: chicken velvet soup
directions: Blend butter and flour in double boiler.
Add warm milk and 2 cups of the chicken stock.
Stir until smooth.
Add cream and cook 15 minutes.
Add remaining 2 cups chicken stock.
Just before serving, stir in chicken and seasonings.
Add more seasoning, if desired.
Serve hot with a sprinkle of chopped parsley.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all together in large bowl. Put in baking dish and bake about 30 minutes at 325°.

title: old-fashion iron skillet corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and heat #6 iron skillet.
After skillet is hot, put enough shortening in skillet (preferable bacon drippings) so when melted there will be excess in skillet.
Put skillet back in oven.
Let grease heat to sizzling stage.
While skillet is heating, beat eggs until light; add buttermilk and beat well.
Measure cornmeal, then add to egg mixture.
Also, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour batter into hot skillet and bake until golden brown and firm, about 30 minutes.
Turn out of pan onto plate.
Cut into wedges.
Serve hot.

title: irish scones
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking soda, salt and egg. Add melted stick of margarine. Mix well. Batter will be very thick. Add buttermilk and raisins; mix well. Batter is sticky and stiff. With hands, make 3 balls of batter and slice each ball in half, then slice half again to loosely form a triangle. Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° for about 23 to 30 minutes. Makes 1 dozen scones.

title: butterscotch crisps
directions: Melt over low heat.
Add chow mein noodles and stir until well coated.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper lined on cookie sheet. Chill until set.

title: baked salmon
directions: Slice potatoes and onions very thin.
Boil for 5 minutes, add salt and pepper to taste.
In 9 inch baking dish, buttered, place a layer of potatoes, a layer of onions, layer of salmon and catsup.
Repeat this until all ingredients are used.
bake a 350 degrees for 40 - 50 minutes.

title: green bean casserole 2
directions: In a large bowl, add drained green beans, mushroom soup, 1/2 cup milk, soy sauce, pepper and about 2/3 can onion rings. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with remaining onion rings and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Cook onion and green pepper in oleo. Add flour and blend.
Add milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken soup, then chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use greased casserole.

title: maw maw byar's tea cakes
directions: Mix all together; set in refrigerator for 30 minutes to rise. Roll out in little balls and flatten.
Bake on low temperature until golden.

title: healthy cashew nut loaf
directions: Mix all.
Place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and spices.
Pour Vernors and chili sauce over beef and simmer until Vernors is absorbed, usually about an hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine sweet potatoes and all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell; bake for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 325° and bake for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: sausage in a bun
directions: Arrange sausage in spoke fashion on a pie plate.
Cover with paper towel and microwave on High for 3 minutes, rotating dish after 1 1/2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Blend in melted margarine, brown sugar, egg and vanilla. Combine all ingredients together and stir well.
Spoon into 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup butterscotch bits.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook together the hamburger meat and onion; drain once done. Mix the soups, enchilada sauce and taco sauce with hamburger and onion. In large casserole dish, alternate Doritos and sauce mixture. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: beef burritos in red sauce
directions: Brown stew meat; drain grease.
Add onion, tomatoes, tomato paste, cumin and garlic powder.
Cook 2 hours in skillet, stirring occasionally, or 6 hours in crock-pot.
Remove beef and shred with 2 forks.
Mix half of the sauce in the beef.
Add 1/2 cup water to remaining sauce.
Spoon meat onto the middles of the tortillas. Fold the sides and ends of the tortillas.
Arrange burritos in a baking dish.
Cover with the remaining sauce.
Top with cheese. Place under broiler until cheese melts.

title: coconut sour cream dream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions, making two 8-inch layers. Split layers horizontally after cooled. Blend together the sugar, sour cream and coconut and chill. Spread all but 1 cup of the sour cream mixture between the 4 layers. Blend the remaining cup of mixture with the whipped topping and spread on top and sides of the cake. Seal in an airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving. Keep refrigerated after cutting.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Cool.
Mix sugar, Crisco and vanilla with first mixture with electric mixer on highest speed for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: frosting
directions: Beat all together with electric mixer.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown, season to taste and drain meat.
Stir in the pizza sauce, mushrooms, olives, pepperoni and Italian seasonings.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in a greased muffin tin, pressing to cover bottom and sides. Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuit-lined cups and sprinkle generously with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 pizza cups.

title: delicious blueberry cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and beaten egg; cream together, then add milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and cinnamon; add to the mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir in berries carefully, not to mash. Bake in 8 x 8-inch greased pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Also, can be put in muffin tins.

title: mom's stuffed shells
directions: Cook and drain shells according to package directions.
Rinse in cold water.
Cook ground beef and add diced pepper and onion. Cook broccoli heads until tender and mash lightly.
Add cream cheese to broccoli and then mix into hamburger mixture.

title: sausage (ham) souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease.
Mix and beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and dry mustard.
Add cubed bread and stir.
Add cheese and sausage (ham); put in greased baking dish (glass).
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand.
Serves 8.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix together and spread on flour tortilla.
Roll up and put in icebox to set.
Slice in bite size to serve.

title: maryland style vegetable crab soup
directions: Brown the meat.
Add about 6 quarts water, soup starter, Worcestershire sauce, Old Bay and tomato puree.
Simmer until meat is tender (about 2 to 3 hours).
Add crab meat and vegetables. Simmer, covered, until vegetables are done.
Add Old Bay as needed.

title: turkey lasagne
directions: Boil noodles in water for 10 to 15 minutes or until done but not mushy.
Drain in colander and run cold water over them. Meanwhile, cook gravy, adding parsley to pan.

title: fresh vegetables(le legumes macadoine)
directions: Peel and cube or slice vegetables.
When root vegetables are cooked (resistant to the bite), add the frozen vegetables and add ice to cool.
(Do not strain cooking water).
Let vegetables set in water for 10 minutes before use.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Dust nuts, dates and candy in 1/2 cup flour.
Add milk and remaining flour alternately.
Add orange slices, nuts, coconut and dates.
Pour in tube pan and bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Glaze with 2 cups powdered sugar mixed with 1 cup frozen orange juice.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground meat.
Mix up cornbread mix according to directions on pkg.
Put half of cornbread mix in baking dish then put ground meat.
Next put cream corn on top of meat and then add cheese and then the rest of the cornbread mix.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: sweet freezer pickles
directions: Add salt to cucumbers and let stand for 2 hours. Drain.
Add onion to cucumbers.
Mix the sugar and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers and onion.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Stir 1 to 2 times. Put in containers and freeze.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until well mixed.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into loaf pans (3).
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: tuna cashew salad
directions: Drain tuna and mix with chopped celery, chopped olives, chopped carrots and chopped onions.
Add nuts and Chinese noodles just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: giant cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar together until light and fluffy. Blend in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt together.
Add to margarine and sugar.
Stir in 1/2 cup candies and 1/4 cup nuts.
Place dough on foil lined, lightly greased 12 to 13-inch pizza pan.
Spread dough to within 1 1/2-inch of edge of pan.
Sprinkle remaining candies, etc. over dough.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Combine sugars and water.
Bring to a boil; boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and gradually add coffee.	Cool ten minutes.
Add vanilla and vodka.	Mix thoroughly.
Cover and let stand for 3 weeks.
Very good.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Season with whatever you season dried beans.
Cook vegetables as beans are cooking.
Stir occasionally as this thickens the beans.
Salt to taste when beans are tender.

title: mrs. d's taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and chili beans in skillet over medium-high heat.
Drain excess grease, then set aside to cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, baking as for 2 layers.
Combine pudding with cold milk.
Tear 1 layer of baked cake into bite-size pieces and place on bottom of pan or dish.
Pour prepared pudding over cake.
Tear up second cake layer and scatter over pudding.
Layer on crushed pineapple and the pie filling.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish with nuts and fruit.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Pour cracker crumbs in pie plate, add butter and sugar.
Heat in oven until butter melts.
Set aside.
Pour Eagle Brand milk in bowl, add whipped eggs, stir, then add lemon juice and stir until thick.
Pour into crust.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, cinnamon, cloves and 3/4 cup melted butter. Add vanilla, mashed potatoes, salt, pecans, milk and water.
Stir in flour with mixture.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add raisins.
Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes in oven at 300° in 3 cake pans.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Roll out.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350 for 8 minutes.

title: swedish egg kake(a breakfast treat)
directions: Blend first five ingredients.
Melt butter/margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients in blender, pour in pan. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
It will rise and then fall upon removal from oven.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil large sliced medium thickness potatoes and onion, sliced thin, until you can fork potatoes and are done.
Drain and butter casserole dish.
Put layer of potatoes, onions, salt, pepper and cheese.
Then repeat.
Place in microwave or oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: company cabbage
directions: Heat butter in large skillet.
Add cabbage, garlic and 1/4 cup water.
Cover tightly and steam over low heat 10 to 12 minutes. Blend next 4 ingredients, stir into cabbage.
Heat through but do not boil.
Sprinkle with caraway seed.
Serves 6.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients; do not cook.
Freeze.

title: corn pie
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add tomatoes; mix in corn and muffin mix.
Add to this, the egg, onion, cheese and tomato mixture.
Turn into a greased dish (use 8 x 8-inch pan) and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Chop and cook squash and onions.
Mix in bowl the squash, onion, bread crumbs, eggs and bacon bits.
Add melted margarine. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top while hot.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Just before serving, mix all ingredients together.

title: soft pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar gradually. Add oil, anise oil and vanilla and mix. Add flour, soda and powder; mix until smooth. If dough is too runny, add a little more flour. Bake in pizzelle iron 30 to 35 seconds.

title: berry time shortcake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In small bowl combine all cake ingredients except strawberries and whipped cream.
Beat at medium speed 1 to 2 minutes.
Spread into greased and floured 9-inch baking pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely. Cut into squares.
Serve with strawberries and sweetened whipped cream.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine with chicken and dressings.
Let marinate several hours or overnight.
Add remaining ingredients; toss and chill.
Delicious!!!

title: breakfast bread
directions: Mix together the buttermilk, honey, molasses, soda and salt. In another bowl, combine the whole wheat flour and white flour; add that blend to the buttermilk mixture.
Stir in the raisins. Pour the batter into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Preheat your oven to 400°, turn it back to 350° and slide in the pan.
Bake the bread for 1 hour.
Turn the loaf out, inverted, onto a rack to cool.
Wait 1 day before slicing and toasting this breakfast bread.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Pound chicken breasts until flat; set aside.
Mix 2 tablespoons of butter, lemon pepper and salt; set aside.
Melt remaining butter and allow to cool.

title: deviled pork chops
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; simmer 20 minutes. Add next 2 ingredients. Pour over chops. Bake in slow 325° oven for 1 hour and 50 minutes or until done. Turn chops over.

title: lemon lu
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs and bananas. Beat until fluffy.
Combine salt, baking powder, baking soda and flour. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk. Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in nuts and vanilla extract. Grease or line with 12 muffin cups about 1/2 capacity.
Divide batter among cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: perfect meringue
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 1 tablespoon of cold water.
Add 1/2 cup water and cook until thick and clear.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and beat until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Add cooled mixture to beaten egg whites and spread on pie.
Bake at 350° until brown (12 to 15 minutes).

title: christmas fudge ring
directions: Melt morsels with milk in double boiler over hot water.
When mixture begins to thicken, remove from heat and add coarsely chopped nuts and vanilla. Chill 1 hour.
Line the bottom of a 9-inch pie pan with a 12-inch square of foil.
Place 3/4 cup walnut halves in bottom of pan forming a 2-inch wide ring. Spoon mixture in small mounds on top of walnuts forming ring.
Decorate with remaining walnut halves.

title: brown sugar seafoam candy
directions: Boil sugar and water until forms a hard ball in cold water. Remove from heat and stir slowly into stiffly beaten egg white until it becomes thick.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon into buttered pan or waxed paper.
Makes 1 pound.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes. Start timing after mixture reaches a full, rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Beat until blended, then drop on waxed paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: fruit floaters
directions: Wash fruit; place in ice cube trays.
Pour lemonade over fruit and freeze.
To serve, pour ginger ale or Sprite over ice in tall glasses.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and make balls.
Place in baking dish. Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls. Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: refrigerator rolls(yeast bread)
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour hot water over sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 1/2 cups of flour and mix thoroughly.
Stir in softened yeast, half of remaining flour and egg.
Beat thoroughly.
Add enough flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Let rest 5 to 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down.
Grease top.
Cover with damp towel and refrigerate.
When ready to bake, shape into rolls and place in well-greased pan.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen rolls.

title: cornbread dressing casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in large casserole dish for 1 hour at 400°. Serves 10 people.

title: magic fudge
directions: Melt chocolate morsels.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, vanilla, nuts and salt.
Spread into waxed paper lined 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Turn fudge to cutting board and cut into squares.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine egg and catsup.
Stir in cheese, bread crumbs, onions, green pepper, salt, thyme and pepper.
Add ground beef; mix well. In an 11 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, shape meat mixture into a 6-inch round loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour, or until done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fettuccine with creamy mustard chicken sauce
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook fettuccine until just tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Return pasta to pot. Add cream and mustard to pasta in pot.
Cook over medium heat, tossing, until well mixed and hot, about 2 minutes.
Mix in chicken and red peppers.
Heat through.
Serve immediately.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine meat, salt, water, breadcrumbs and egg.
Mix well and shape into small balls.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, tomato sauce and lemon juice in a saucepan.
Simmer about 3 minutes.
Add meatballs and continue to simmer about 45 minutes.
Transfer to a chafing dish.
Set on low heat.
Garnish with lemon slices or parsley (if desired).
Yield: 3 1/2 dozen.

title: old fashion egg custard pies
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shells.
Top with sliced margarine. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make the pudding.
Add the wafers on top of the pudding, then add the bananas on top of the wafers.
Add more pudding on top of the wafers.
Put in refrigerator until cold, then eat.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a bowl, combine rice, beef, salt, pepper and onion.
Mix well and shape into 12 balls. Brown balls in hot fat in heavy frypan.
Add tomato soup and water. Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours over low heat until nice and tender.

title: carrot cream mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Gradually add to sour cream, stirring until well blended.
Chill until syrupy.
Add pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Pour into 2 quart mold and chill until firm.
Serve on a bed of greens.

title: killer clam chowder
directions: Take liquid from clams and add water to make 2 cups.
Cook potatoes and onion in pan, covered, for 15 minutes or until tender.
Stir in clams and cream.
Add rest of ingredients, heat and serve.

title: good egg custard pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix sugar and flour with mixer.
Add margarine and vanilla; mix.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk.
Pour into ungreased pie plate.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes; turn the oven back to 200° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Take cake pan and spray with Pam and flour lightly.
Put nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix like box says.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Put on top of cake mix by dropping with tablespoon.
Put in oven and bake until done.

title: peanut butter autumn spotlights
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, peanut butter, margarine, water and eggs; stir until well blended.
Fold in candy pieces.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets. Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: busy women's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Crush garlic clove and mix into butter.
Let stand at least one hour.
Remove garlic.
Mix bread crumbs, cheeses, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in butter, then in cheese mixture.
Place in baking pan, tucking sides of breasts under to form neat rolls.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Baste occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: make over dill pickles
directions: Drain juice out of 1/2 gallon of pickles. Cut pickles into thick chunks and put back into jar. Mix vinegar, sugar and water in saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour mixture over pickles in jar while hot still. If mixture doesn't cover pickles, add a little more water. Turn jar upside down and leave for a while.

title: souper meat-n-potato pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup of the soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings.
Firmly press the mixture into a 9-inch pie plate, forming a shell, and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Spoon off any fat.
Frost with mashed potatoes and top with remaining soup and cheese.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes more.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix meat, onion, vegetables and gravy.
Divide between 2 ungreased 1-quart casseroles.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Put 1 in freezer and bake the other at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift and measure together flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add shortening, margarine and milk; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, beating well one at a time.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Drain.
Melt butter and brown meat.
Stir in sauce and flour; simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream, salt, onions, green pepper, olives and soup.
Grease a baking dish.
Put 3/4 of noodles in dish.
Spread on all cheese mixture; add rest of noodles.
Top with ground beef mixture.
You may add grated cheese to top.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: kane's crawfish fettucine
directions: Saute vegetables in butter 20 minutes. Add seasonings and soup and cook 5 minutes. Add tails and cook 3 minutes. Add cream and cheese chunks slowly. Stir in parsley and Parmesan. Add mixture to cooked and drained noodles. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or more.

title: spaghetti with eggs and bacon
