directions: Combine the pancetta and chili pepper in a skillet and cook over low heat until some of the fat has melted.
Increase the heat and cook until the pancetta browns.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a large bowl, sift all dry ingredients together.
Add to first four ingredients.
Mix in 3 cups of diced apples and 1 cup nuts.
Mix by hand.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch pan with Pam.
Mix butter, flour and powdered sugar.
Pat into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chili
directions: Dice onions, carrots, peppers and celery; cook mixture in oil with 1 to 1/4 ratio of oil/olive oil (1/4 the amount of olive oil versus vegetable oil).
Cook until there is no crunch to the onions.
Mix the 28-ounce can of tomatoes with the mixer, leaving some chunks to tomatoes.
Pour the small can of tomatoes in the blender.
Add the spices; blend this until smooth.
Put the mixture in a pan; cook for 4 1/2 minutes.
Cook the meats until done.
Mix the tomato mixture, sauce and meat together; simmer for 22 minutes.
Taste for saltiness and spice heat.
If it is not spicy enough, put in jalapeno sauce or cayenne pepper until it satisfies your taste.

title: chili sauce
directions: Tie spices in loose weave cloth. Combine all ingredients in large pot. Cook for 2 1/2 hours. Can in hot jars.

title: crab dip
directions: Heat cheese and soup in saucepan.
Add gelatin.
Remove from heat.
Add celery, onion, crab, and mayonnaise.

title: red bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough Miracle Whip to mix ingredients well.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add milk and molasses to bran and let stand 2 minutes; add egg and shortening and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add, stirring only until combined.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffins.

title: pineapple refrigerator pie
directions: Roll vanilla wafers fine and put half in pie dish, pressing down firmly.
Cream sugar and butter and add well beaten eggs. Pour in on crumbs, then pineapple that has been well drained.
Add nuts to whipped cream, then put this over top of pineapple.
Then, other half of crumbs on top and sides. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Combine buttermilk, eggs and oil.
Stir raisins into dry ingredients.
Combine milk mixture into dry ingredients.
Stir only until blended.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in greased pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt oleo (1 cup), add crumbs and sugar.
Mix well.
Press on sides and bottom.
Beat 2 sticks butter, powdered sugar and 2 eggs at least 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Lay sliced bananas, pineapple, Cool Whip, nuts and cherries over the top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: three c. bread
directions: In a large bowl, sift dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, oil and milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add carrots, coconut and cherries. Divide dough into 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: helen's beef jerky
directions: Marinate overnight.
Drain on paper towel and bake in 250° oven for 2 hours.
Turn oven off and leave in oven until next morning.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Pour liquid over breasts.
Cover with foil. Bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours.
Remove foil the last 3/4 hour. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: candy cookies(microwave)
directions: Place
milk
and
margarine in large glass mixing bowl. Microwave
on
High
for 1 minute.	Add salt, cocoa and sugar; mix well.
Microwave
on
High
for
to 6 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring occasionally.
Add vanilla and peanut butter. Blend
well.
Add
oatmeal;
stir
until
well mixed. Drop	by spoonfuls onto foil or preferably waxed paper.
Chill until firm or let set until firm.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Cream well shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Sift together salt, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Add nuts if desired and chopped apples.
Bake 35-40 minutes in a 350 degree oven in a greased and floured 8x8 pan.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, molasses and eggs in a large bowl.
Add flour, soda, salt, ginger, cloves and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add boiling water; blend well.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: quiche
directions: Arrange crumbled bacon, onion and Swiss cheese over bottom of pie crusts.
Mix together half and half and seasonings.
Pour carefully into pie crusts.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and then at 300° for 35 minutes.
Make sure it is set in middle.

title: northrup special
directions: Fry cubed potatoes until done.
Place in bottom of 2 to 3-inch sided baking pan.
Salt lightly.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Open chili and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle onions and cheese over chili.
Place in oven and bake until heated through and cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: hot juice
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat on low until hot.

title: meatball and macaroni supper
directions: *You may use prepared spaghetti sauce in place of these ingredients.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Brown beef; add onion, garlic, celery, pepper and salt.
Add combined tomato paste, tomato juice, chili powder, cayenne pepper and curry powder.
Cook until all ingredients are done.
Cook spaghetti as package directs.
When done, add enough meat sauce to spaghetti to prevent spaghetti from sticking together.
Place serving of spaghetti on plate and cover with meat sauce.

title: spinach pie superb
directions: Cook spinach according to directions and drain well. (Squeeze!)
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Stir in spinach.
Pour into slightly baked pie shell.
Slice and place tomato on top. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 450° (preheated oven) for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: japanese mandarin orange cake
directions: *Use 1/2 cup juice in cake and 1/2 cup juice in sugar glaze.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix one at a time, in order given.
Cook on medium heat.
Stir constantly until thickens.
Let cool.
Stir every 5 minutes.
Pour into cooked crust, or graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: christmas cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and shortening; mix well.
Fold in remaining ingredients and pour into two 9-inch pans or three 8-inch pans.
Frost with Divinity Frosting.

title: deep fried ice cream
directions: Soften ice cream enough to make into a ball.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and freeze overnight.
Wrap ice cream in pie crust and seal edges.
Heat deep fryer to 425° or hotter.
Drop ice cream into fryer.
When it comes to the top, about 2 seconds, it is done. Cover with your favorite topping.
This can be made into individual servings by making smaller balls.

title: quick dump cake
directions: In a baking pan, dump pineapple with juice and cherry pie filling.
Top with cake mix.
Pat with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold with ice cream.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken into egg.
On wax paper, coat chicken with crumbs.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in butter, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In skillet lightly cook beef, onion and pepper.
Drain fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Place in small or large bread pan. For small pan, bake at 350° for 1 hour.
For large pan, bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Combine egg, 1/3 c. pizza sauce, bread crumbs and beef.
Mix together and form into two loaves.
Top lower loaf with 1/2 c. mozzarella cheese and 1/4 parmesan cheese and parsley. Put top loaf over mixture and seal meat around edges.Cook in Microwave- in a drain pan- cover with wax paper.
Cook on Hi for 5 minutes. - drain- then medium (50%) for 12 minutes. -drain- let stand 10 minutes. Warm rest of pizza sauce and pour over and top with rest of mozzarella cheese.

title: nifty fifty dip
directions: Combine ingredients; beat until smooth.
Cover; chill to blend flavors.
Before serving, allow dip to soften to room temperature. Serve as a dip for potato chips, fancy crackers or raw vegetables.

title: berliner kranser or wreaths
directions: Beat yolks real good.
Gradually add sugar and cream and beat until stiff.
Stir in part of the flour.
Place enough dough on breadboard, spreading on softened butter.
Fold batter, then spread on more butter.
Continue process until butter and flour are all used up.
After each addition, pound with rolling pin until thoroughly mixed.
Set in a cool place until chilled.

title: southern-style cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, margarine and eggs, mixing just until moistened.
Pour into well-greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sweet sauerkraut
directions: Cook 10 minutes in skillet.
Add water if necessary.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Add hot water to jello and cranberry juice mix well. Add nuts, pineapple and celery. Refrigerate until congealed, and store in refrigerate until serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, eggs, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Slowly mix in the flour, soda and salt.
Once all the dry ingredients are mixed, add the chips and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: crab casserole
directions: Blend milk and mayonnaise; fold in remaining ingredients, except cheese and cereal.
Put in greased baking dish; sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with foil and put in fridge overnight.
Take out one hour before baking; crush cereal on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn dogs
directions: Stir milk into dry ingredients.
Add melted shortening.
For deep frying, dip wieners in batter, holding with a fork or skewer. Drain excess batter back into bowl.
Fry in wire basket until golden brown at 375°.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate oatmeal clusters(no-bake cookies)
directions: Bring sugar, butter, cocoa, milk and salt to a boil in a medium saucepan for 1 minute.
Then stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop on wax paper.
Let cool until hard.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving-size pieces.
Coat with flour, salt and pepper.
In large electric skillet, brown meat.
Place stewed tomatoes, chopped onion, chopped green pepper and mushrooms over steak.
Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours (at 200° to 225°). Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Place raw rice in bottom of casserole dish with a cover.
Add soups and mushrooms.
Mix all together.
Slice the stick of margarine into patties on top.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: grilled flank steak
directions: Score flank steak on both sides and marinate in the dressing for at least 4 hours.
Grill 4 minutes on each side and slice diagonally to serve.
Serve with small rolls, assorted mustards and mayonnaise.

title: cola glazed ham
directions: Soak the ham overnight.
Place rind side down in a roasting pan.
Pour over all but 3 tablespoons of soda.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 2 1/2 hours, basting frequently. Remove the ham from the oven; let cool for 15 minutes.
Remove rind from ham; score the fat to a depth of 1/2 inch.
Stick a clove in center of every other diamond on ham.
Mix together the sugar and the remaining cola; spoon over ham.
Raise oven temperature to 375° and bake for 5 minutes.
Baste frequently. Allow to stand for 15 minutes before slicing.

title: pear salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on box using 1/2 cup pear juice with cold water.
Let jell.
Soften cream cheese with a little of the Jell-O mixture while warm (using a fork).
Drain pears well and cut up.
Whip Dream Whip.
Whip Jell-O and add softened cheese and whip some more.
Fold in Dream Whip and pears; return to the refrigerator.
Makes a large salad.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Coat nuts with egg white.
Add sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place nuts on cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook and clean shrimp.
Make bread crumbs by crumbling toast.* Combine shrimp, bread crumbs, eggs, seasonings, onions and bell pepper with a tablespoon of melted margarine in greased casserole dish.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Save broth.
Cook English peas and add to chicken.
Add soups and broth.
Melt margarine and stir in flour and milk.
Put chicken and peas in baking dish.
Pour flour mixture over this.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mother's christmas divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Blend thoroughly over heat until the sugar dissolves.
Cook without stirring until syrup reaches 270° on a candy thermometer.
Pour syrup slowly over egg whites.
Beat until mixture holds its shape and does not flatten out after it has set.
Add nuts, cherries and flavoring.
Mix until mixture begins to lose some of its gloss.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Line cooled pie shell with 2 cups blueberries.

title: apple crumble
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in butter.
Mix until crumbly. Arrange apples in greased shallow pan.
Sprinkle apples with dry mixture and bake at 350° about 30 minutes until brown.

title: fudgy fudge cake
directions: Combine and bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa, shortening and water.
Sift together and add to hot mixture the flour and sugar.
Combine and add to mixture the eggs, soda, vanilla, buttermilk and salt.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blackberry rolli bolli
directions: Beat together Bisquick and enough water to make mixture of a biscuit consistency.
Pour out on floured board and roll out to about 1/4-inch thick (10 to 12 inches in diameter).
Spread with blackberries (still frozen is best).
Roll up like a jelly roll. Fit into round casserole bowl.
Mix 1 cup of water with 1 cup of sugar.
Pour over blackberry roll and bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: golden fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together to dissolve sugar.
Cool.
Add frozen fruit juices, ginger ale and remaining chilled water just before serving.

title: baked french toast
directions: Line bottom of 11 x 13-inch pan with half the bread cubes. Layer cream cheese on top of bread.
Arrange remaining bread cubes on top.

title: low cost sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Keeps several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break some cake up in the bottom of the punch bowl. Then put 1/2 of pudding, cherry pie filling, bananas, pineapple and cool whip. Repeat layers starting with the cake. If you like on top of cool whip, you can use chopped nuts.

title: 4-layer dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup chopped nuts, 1/2 cup butter and 2 tablespoons sugar together and press into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: easy barbecue chicken wings
directions: Cut off tips of wings and split; wash and pat dry.
Marinate wings in sauce for about an hour.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Double recipe if desired.

title: danish red cabbage
directions: Remove outer leaves and core from cabbage.
Shred cabbage very fine.
Melt butter in large pot.
Add cabbage, vinegar
or lemon juice, salt and sugar; stir to distribute.
Cover and cook over low heat until cabbage is tender, about 20 minutes.
Stir in jelly if desired.
Serve hot.

title: meringue
directions: In the large bowl of an electric mixer, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, salt and vanilla and beat until stiff peaks form.
Pile on top of mixture in pie shell. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion.
Mix in bread cubes and chicken.
Put into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Beat eggs with fork.
Add soup, milk and poultry seasoning.
Mix well and pour over stuffing.
Combine flour and cheese.
Cut margarine into cheese mixture and sprinkle evenly over top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: jane's candy strawberries
directions: Mix ingredients and form into strawberries. Dip in red sugar, place on paper and refrigerate!

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in a large pan until done, stirring frequently to keep from sticking.
Serve on buns.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: *Note:
To be sure mold is extra firm (especially in hot weather), add 1 package unflavored gelatin to the orange gelatin before dissolving in hot water.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: In a bowl, combine sugar, flour and 3/4 cup buttermilk. Add eggs and remaining buttermilk; mix well. Stir in butter and vanilla. Divide evenly among pie shells. Top with pecans, if desired. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean. Cool completely. Store in refrigerator.

title: ham and broccoli quiche
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: daddy's lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine milk and egg yolks; blend in juice.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add sugar gradually continuing to beat until stiff.
Spoon meringue over pie and bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Combine shrimp, Cheddar cheese and cream cheese with fingers. Form ball.
Pat with chopped walnuts.

title: curried pork chops
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a bag.
Dredge chops in mixture. Rub skillet with a clove and brown chops on both sides.
Place in casserole in layers with 4 or 5 sliced potatoes and cover with mushrooms.
Heat shortening in skillet.
Brown leftover flour mixture with milk and juice from mushrooms.
Cook over low heat until brown and thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over chops. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cream together sugar and egg yolks.
Add noodles, melted butter or margarine, cottage cheese and sour cream to mixture. Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan and top with Frosted Flakes and butter.
Bake 30 minutes in preheated 375° oven.

title: squash pie
directions: Cut squash; cook until tender.
Drain off water.
Mash fine. Add eggs and nutmeg.
Add milk to thin.
Add vanilla.
Mix well. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish with butter.
Line bottom of dish with Zesta crackers.
Put cooked broccoli on top of crackers.
Put 1 stick oleo (diced) over broccoli.
Put Velveeta cheese (diced) over broccoli.
Melt 3 tablespoons oleo and mixed with crushed Zesta crackers until crumbly.
Put crumbs over mixture.
Put casserole in 300° oven until the cheese is melted.

title: oven-roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place potatoes in 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) or 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) baking dish.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour margarine mixture over potatoes. Toss to coat evenly. Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes or until tender, crisp and lightly browned, stirring twice during baking.

title: best rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large container and let rise about 4 hours or overnight.
Separate into 3 parts.
Roll out on floured board.
Roll thin.
Cut in strips.
Put melted margarine over dough.
Use strips to form crescent rolls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 4 hours.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli and sauce.
Put in buttered 7 x 12-inch casserole dish. Put grated cheese on top.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: filet mignon in red wine
directions: Combine salt pork, garlic and butter in a skillet; heat.
Add the steaks and cook on each side for 4 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and wine.
Cover and cook for 2 minutes.
Add parsley and shake skillet.
Place steaks on warm plate and strain juice on top of meat.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, bread crumbs and salt together.
Shape into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Brown in broiler.
Put meatballs and all other ingredients in crock-pot and stir.
Heat on High until bubbles (approximately 15 minutes), then turn down, stirring occasionally.

title: 5-6 bean crock-pot
directions: Cook on low in a crock-pot for 3 or 4 hours.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Mix vanilla pudding, 3 cups milk and Cool Whip together.
Boil sugar, 1/4 cup milk, cocoa, vanilla and margarine together; set aside.
Line bottom of large glass dish with broken graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of pudding over crackers, then line crackers again.
Add pudding mixture and line with cocoa mixture.
Add pudding again and pour remaining chocolate on top.

title: party punch
directions: Put dry lemonade Kool-Aid in gallon jug. Add pineapple juice. Finish filling jug with water.
Mix well and chill.
Shake very well and pour in punch bowl. Add ginger ale.

title: cranberry orange delight salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling cranberry-apple juice. Stir in carbonated beverage. Chill until syrupy. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into a 1 1/2 quart mold. Chill until firm. Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal-bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine milk, oil and egg; stir into flour mixture.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: black bean soup
directions: Pick over and wash beans. Add appropriate water and bring to a boil over stove or in a crock-pot. Add remaining ingredients. Use toppings of choice.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Mix first four ingredients in large saucepan.
Dissolve very slowly over low heat.
Turn off burner and add orange juice and lemonade.
Store in refrigerator until ready to reheat and serve.

title: russian cutlettas(serves 4)
directions: *Use only if using salmon.

title: spinach marie
directions: Mix ingredients and enjoy.

title: green mountain chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove lid and bake 30 minutes.

title: oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish and melt in the oven.
Mix eggs, sour cream, milk and salt.
Stir in chives.
Bake at 350°for about 35 minutes or until eggs are set, but still moist.

title: granny's cherry cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Divide flour.
Add first two cups to the mixture.
Add baking powder and salt to the last cup of flour.
Add this to the mixture.
Add milk, vanilla and cherries.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Add baking soda to applesauce.
Mix brown sugar and shortening, then add to applesauce.
Mix applesauce mixture with the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: one egg banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Stir in all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat again.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and allspice together three times.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with sour milk.
Fold in jam.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° about 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove from pans and complete cooling on wire racks.
Frost with frosting.

title: reese's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except only 1/2 cup peanut butter cups. Chill.
Top with remaining peanut butter cups.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour and salt in pan. Add milk. Cook on low heat. Add your egg yolks (slightly beaten) to mixture. Cook until thick. Add your butter and vanilla. Stir and pour in pie shell. Beat egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar. Put on chocolate pie. Bake in 350° oven 15 minutes or until meringue is brown.

title: 30 day cake
directions: At the end of 30 days drain liquid from fruit.
Divide the liquid into 4 or 5 jars (1-1/2 cups) and give away.
Divide fruit into thirds.

title: mexican dip
directions: Saute onion and peppers.
In a separate frying pan, fry hamburger and pork sausage.
Add sauteed onion and peppers to hamburger and pork sausage mixture.
Add crushed tomatoes to the mixture and simmer for 15 minutes.
Layer the hamburger and pork sausage mixture with the Velveeta cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: kentucky wonder pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients, except nuts.
Beat well.
Add the floured nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/4 hours at 325°.

title: chicken loaf(yield:  18 servings)
directions: Make white sauce of the stock, milk, flour and oleo.
Combine all ingredients.
Pack well into loaf pans; set loaf pans in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Let stand 20 minutes before slicing.
Serve with rich chicken gravy.

title: pecan fudge
directions: Boil ingredients to soft ball stage (242°).
Set aside until cold, beat until creamy, then add nuts and pour into a pan.
When cold, cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients but butter and crumbs.
Place in a casserole and cover with crumbs.
Pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cream cheese and salad dressing until smooth.
Add pecans and garlic powder.
Serve with crackers or toasted bread squares.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Note:
Need foil cupcake liners and muffin pan.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Slice onions thin and soak for 2 to 4 hours in sugar, vinegar and water.
Drain well.
Toss with mayonnaise and celery salt. Serve on saltine crackers, hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles; drain.
Cook hamburger; drain and then mix with Ragu sauce.
Layer in this order in a 9 x 12-inch pan:
3 noodles, meat/spaghetti sauce, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, 3 noodles, cottage cheese, meat sauce, 3 noodles, the rest of the meat sauce and cover with the remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chop chicken up fine.
Mix well.
Add mayonnaise to your taste.

title: pear or pineapple cream cheese spread
directions: Combine preserves and horseradish; spoon over cream cheese. Serve with date nut bread or crackers.

title: frankfurter and peas casserole
directions: Cut hot dogs into 1/4 slices; brown lightly in margarine. Remove hot dogs and set aside.
Add flour to margarine in skillet and stir until smooth; add milk, stirring constantly, until thick. Season with salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Mix hot dogs, cheese and peas and pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Pour sauce over mixture.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 or 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bohemian christmas braid
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine milk, sugar and shortening. Cool to lukewarm, add to yeast.
Beat in eggs and half the flour. Add lemon rind, mace, salt, raisins and nuts.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead dough until smooth.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled (about 1 hour).
Divide dough equally in half and each half into thirds.
Roll out into long roll and make braid.
Shape into circle, pinching ends together.
Let rise until light.
Brush with mixture of 1 beaten egg yolk and 2 tablespoons milk before placing in oven.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice and decorate with maraschino cherries when cool. Makes 2 braids.

title: mom's old-fashioned filled cookies
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Roll out on floured board and cut with round cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Put teaspoonful filling on each round.
Put another round of cookie dough on top.
(Don't need to pinch together.)
Bake at 350° for about 11 minutes.

title: shredded beef enchiladas
directions: Cover meat with water and cook in crock pot with taco seasoning.
Meat must be cooked until it is falling apart.
When done drain and let cool.
Shred meat.
Assemble enchiladas by putting meat in middle of tortilla, adding cheese, onion and olives.
Roll up.
Continue until most ingredients are gone (save some cheese for garnish).
Place assembled enchiladas in baking pan (bottom of boiler pan is good).
Blend enchilada sauces and ladle over assembled enchiladas.
Top with remaining cheese.

title: reindeer crunchies ii(used with reindeer treats)
directions: Mix "Reindeer Treats" with peanut butter.
Place mixture in the refrigerator for 15 minutes or until ingredients have cooled and hardened.
Shape mixture into a ball to look like a reindeer's head.
Put raisins where eyes and nose go.
Push antlers into head.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: half-a-pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening until light; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla; combine cake flour and baking powder; add to cream mixture.
Add milk and beat 5 minutes; pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crab meat triangles
directions: Mix seasonings, crab meat, softened margarine, cheese (room temperature) and mayonnaise.
Spread on the 12 halves of English muffins.
Cut each half into 4 pieces.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Do not thaw before baking.

title: green congealed salad
directions: Blend together pistachio pudding and crushed pineapple with juice.
Stir in Cool Whip, nuts and marshmallows.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: festive eggnog cake(christmas cake)
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.	Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 3 well-greased
8-inch pans.	Bake 20 minutes.
Prepare cream cheese frosting.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Drain syrup from fruit cocktail and set aside. Combine sugar, salt, soda and flour. Beat egg.
Add egg and drained syrup to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle nuts and brown sugar over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.
Serves 12 or more.

title: crab recipe
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Add crab meat and shrimp and cook on low until shrimp is cooked.
Add half and half and parsley.
Thicken sauce with flour. Serve over noodles and top with cheese or serve with crackers.

title: stew beef casserole
directions: Pour one small can of tomato sauce over top of ingredients. Cook in a large roasting pan, covered.
Cook for 5 hours at 250°. Remove and stir.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.
Use salt and pepper to taste.

title: lemon bread
directions: Measure flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder into a sifter; sift.
Set aside.

title: california medley blend soup
directions: Mix and cook chicken broth, celery, onion and potatoes for about 15 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and mushrooms.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Add soup and cheese. Heat slowly until cheese and soups are melted.

title: sausage-bean chowder
directions: Brown sausage in a Dutch oven, stirring to crumble.
Drain off drippings.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Remove bay leaf before serving.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: dixie chili (cincinnati style)
directions: Place ground beef (do not brown) and remaining ingredients in ice water.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 3 hours or longer.
Serve over spaghetti and top with grated Cheddar cheese for a 3-way.
Add onions for a 4-way.
Serve over a hot dog topped with Cheddar cheese for a Coney Island.

title: chile reyenos squares
directions: Shred cheese.
Grease 9 x 12 baking dish.
Layer cheese and green chilies in dish.
Pour eggs over mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until center is firm. To keep for later: bake & cool.
Cover with foil.
Reheat at 300° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: perked punch
directions: Perk punch in a large coffee pot; put the juices, cider and water to fill pot.
Put the cinnamon, cloves and sugar in basket.

title: plant dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in blender or food processor; set aside. Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix milk, chocolate pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Layer Oreos and pudding mixture, beginning and ending with Oreos. Insert artificial flower or plant into pot of dessert.
Place a few gummy worms around the top.
Worms can also be layered with other ingredients.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat pumpkin, oil, eggs and water together.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened (do not overmix).
Pour into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 80 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and sour cream. Sprinkle with pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken.
Place crumbled crackers over all. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until it bubbles.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Chop beef, green pepper and onion.
Add softened cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix well by hand.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve warm with assorted crackers.

title: ricotta toast
directions: Combine cheese and pepper.
Spread onto bread.
Place on a cookie sheet (cheese side up).
Heat oven at 375°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in center of oven.
If you would like crispy, remove from oven after baked and place under broiler about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain and mix with other ingredients.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: sweet potatoes with orange juice
directions: Combine cooked potatoes, butter, salt, orange juice, sugar and spices.
Heat until hot.
Add marshmallows; heat until melted. This filling can be placed in orange halves with pulp and orange meat removed and baked as individual servings.
Makes 12 halves. Save orange meat for ambrosia.
(This calls for 6 oranges cut in half for 12 servings.)

title: almond bark candy
directions: Melt almond bark.
Add peanut butter and marshmallows, Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Pour into wax paper-lined 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: almond roca bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg, vanilla and flour, last of all.
Spread in 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Break chocolate bar into sections and put on top of cookies; return to oven with temperature off.
Leave a few minutes to soften.
Spread chocolate. Sprinkle nuts.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: holly berries
directions: Heat marshmallows and margarine over low heat.
When mixture is smooth, add vanilla and green coloring.
Stir this mixture into corn flakes and drop on wax paper in small amounts.
Shape into shape of a wreath.
Add a few red candies.

title: fried squash blossoms
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, garlic salt and cumin.
In another bowl, beat egg, milk and oil; add to dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
In a skillet, heat 2 inches of oil to 375°.
Dip blossoms into batter and fry in oil, a few at a time, until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm until serving.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil first five ingredients until tender.
Debone chicken and set aside.
Add noodles to chicken broth and boil 5 to 7 minutes. If mixture is too dry, add a little water.
If mixture is too watery, remove some broth.
Add cream of mushroom soup and mix well.
Add chicken and mix.
Pour in 9 x 14-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Easy to prepare ahead and freeze.
Bake when ready to use.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: In an ovenproof skillet or heavy pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in brown sugar and diced rhubarb.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Pour batter over rhubarb and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn upside-down on plate.
Serve with cream or milk.

title: mace cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together and bake 1 hour (or longer) at 350°.

title: pink arctic freeze salad
directions: Soften cheese, blend in mayonnaise and sugar.
Add fruits and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze.
Partially thaw before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: "delicious" chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place into a Bundt cake pan. Cook in a 350° oven for a minimum of 65 minutes.

title: soda cracker chocolate candy
directions: Line a 15 x 10-inch baking pan with foil and coat with nonstick cooking spray.
Place crackers in rows on foil.

title: baked potatoes
directions: In a casserole dish layer potatoes, onions, mushrooms and bacon.
Pour over some of the Ranch dressing.
Repeat layers until dish is full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until warmed and heated through.

title: apple fritters(yields about 3 dozen)
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl. Add eggs, milk, salad oil and apples. Stir until all ingredients are moistened.	Pour oil for frying into a heavy saucepan to
a
depth of
1/2-inch.
Heat
to frying temperature. Drop batter
by spoonfuls
into hot oil.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Drain on	paper
towel.
Sprinkle
with confectioners sugar.

title: grandma's strawberry shortcake
directions: Put baking powder in flour; add sugar, salt and lard.
Rub up fine.
Stir in the milk and egg.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
To make large cake, double recipe.
Don't use mixer; mix by hand.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onion in butter or oleo. Cook on top of stove until flavors blend (about 30 minutes). Pour over cooked brisket.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop broccoli and boil until tender.
Drain and place in a large bowl.
Add other ingredients except crackers and butter; mix well.
Pour in a large casserole dish and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
In small bowl, combine butter and cracker crumbs.
Top broccoli with crumbs and bake 5 to 10 more minutes.

title: sausage, rice and soup casserole(willadean's)
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix rest of ingredients with browned sausage. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mud pie
directions: Heat the oven to 325°.
Grease a round pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inch, with shortening.
Mix granulated sugar, margarine, vanilla, salt, eggs, flour and cocoa in a medium bowl with a wooden spoon.
Stir in nuts; pour into a pan.
Bake until pick inserted half way between center and edge comes off clean, about 25 minutes. Immediately pick holes in the pie with a wooden pick.
Spread fudge sauce over top and cool completely.

title: strawberry banana dessert
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing at medium speed of electric mixer until blended.
Add all remaining ingredients, except pecans or nuts, and mix well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts or pecans.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, zucchini, vanilla and oil.
Beat lightly.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in two greased loaf pans.

title: you name it dessert
directions: Line a glass baking dish with split Twinkies, gooey side up. Layer with sliced bananas.
Layer with crushed pineapple.
Layer with pudding, mixed according to directions on box.
Layer with whipped topping.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: mom's pickled beets
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil for 4 or 5 minutes so sugar dissolves.
Put one teaspoon of salt in each quart jar; also, a full teaspoon of pickling spice in each jar.
Pour boiling mixture over cooked beets (salt beets some while cooking) and seal.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: texas brisket
directions: You will also need one cook 'n' bag.

title: grandma's squash pie
directions: Combine squash, sugar and spices.
Add eggs and milk.
Pour into pie pans lined with regular pie crust (unbaked).
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 325° until done. Test filling.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together the peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 8 minutes at High, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Cook 2 more minutes on High.
Add baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy. Immediately pour onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Spread out thin.
When cool, break into small pieces.
Makes 1 pound.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut potatoes into 1/8-inch thick slices and soak in cold water.
Drain and dry the potatoes on paper towels.
Use 1 tablespoon butter to grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Spread half the potatoes in the bottom of the dish. Season to taste with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter, cut into small pieces. Arrange remaining potato slices on top.
Sprinkle with seasonings and remaining cheese.
Pour cream over surface and dot with remaining 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake until potatoes are creamy and top is golden brown, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: simply good chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in large pot with water, 1 tsp. salt and 1 tsp. pepper; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Cool chicken slightly; skin and debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Combine chicken, soups, sour cream and 1/2 tsp. pepper; stir well.
Place 1/2 of crushed crackers in lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2 inch baking dish.
Spoon chicken mixture over crackers.
Top with remaining crackers and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until lightly browned. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: biscotti
directions: 11 x 15 Cookie Sheet- Greased;350 degree oven - approximately 30 minutes until light brown and the center springs back when you touch it.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and corn syrup with hand beater.
Mix in pecan halves.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: sherried beef
directions: Season chops.
Spread with cranberry sauce jelly and top with pineapple wedges.
Bake in a slow 325° oven until well done, about 45 minutes.

title: quickie pound cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix together flour, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add butter to batter.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf  pie
directions: Mix together; pat into pie pan (9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Drain grease.
Make enough mashed potatoes for supper.
Pile on top of meat loaf.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Cheddar on top of potatoes.
Bake until cheese melts.
(I have added shredded cheese inside meat loaf; it is good too.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach. Combine all ingredients. Stir to blend. Chill for 1 hour. Serve.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keeps well in the refrigerator. Add more chilies or jalapenos if you like a hotter salsa.
Add onions, chopped, if desired.
Do not freeze.

title: sauteed carrots and onions
directions: Heat margarine in skillet.
Saute onion until yellow.
Add shredded carrots; stir and saute with onion until carrots soften, about 20 minutes on medium-low heat.
(You may add about 1/4 cup water if ingredients get too dry in pan while cooking.)
Saute until water evaporates.

title: brown rice with pine nuts
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions using chicken broth and water as cooking liquid.
Meanwhile in a cold skillet, toast pine nuts over low heat shaking pan to brown nuts evenly. Remove from skillet and save.
Add to skillet the oil and sesame oil and saute vegetables.
Mix pine nuts and vegetables with cooked rice.
Season to taste with soy sauce.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave the chocolate, milk and margarine on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Spread evenly in crust.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Arrange sliced bananas over chocolate.
Pour cold milk in large bowl; add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute. Let stand 5 minutes.
Pour over bananas in crust.
Spread with topping.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and 3 egg yolks.
Add milk alternately with flour.
Fold into egg whites and fruit.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Cook in very slow oven at 300°.

title: batter balls
directions: Mix all together.
Drop in hot grease.
Cool and cover with sugar.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips and nuts. Beat 2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Sift into large bowl the flour, sugar and cinnamon; set aside. Bring
cocoa, butter, water and 1/2 cup Kahlua to boil in medium saucepan.
Pour
over
flour mixture; mix well.
In separate
bowl beat
eggs, soda, buttermilk and 3 tablespoons Kahlua.
Add to flour
mixture.
Mix
well.
Pour
into
x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake
at
for 35 to 40 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: low-fat taco casserole
directions: Brush tortillas with oil, salt and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Mix chili, beans, the two sauces, onion and cheese. Pour over tortillas and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with the yogurt and sour cream and then add the chips.
Contains 15 grams of fat.

title: meatballs with grape sauce
directions: In a large bowl, mix ground beef, eggs, crumbs, water and garlic salt.
Mix well; shape into medium size balls.
In a large skillet, combine chili sauce, grape jelly and lemon juice; mix well.
Add meatballs; cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes until meat is done.
Serve with sauce.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add milk, chocolate and beaten egg yolks.
Cook over hot water until thick.
Cool.
Add vanilla and pour into baked crust.
Use egg whites (room temperature) for meringue.

title: tomato sandwich
directions: Peel tomatoes and slice in small pieces.
Add salt, pepper and mayonnaise to taste.
Toast bread and add the tomato spread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; chop up and drain excess oil.
Saute onions and celery.
Combine onions, celery, melted margarine and chicken and mushroom soups together.
Add broccoli and mix well.
Add rice.

title: lemon extract
directions: Use a vegetable peeler to remove peel from lemon in small strips, being careful not to include white portion.
In a small saucepan, bring lemon peel and vodka to a boil.
Remove from heat. Pour into a small glass jar and seal.
Allow extract to stand at least 2 weeks before using.
Yields about 1/2 cup of extract.

title: trio salad
directions: Mix lime jello by directions on box. Pour in large bowl. Let set in refrigerator until jelled. Mix lemon jello with 2 cups boiling water. Add marshmallows. After they are dissolved (let cool), then add pineapple, Cool Whip, cream cheese, mayonnaise and pecans to lemon mixture and pour over lime jello. Let it set until it is jelled. Mix strawberry jello and pour over lemon mixture. Let set in refrigerator until jelled.

title: elizabeth's pepper bread roll ups
directions: Roll slices of bread as thin as possible with a rolling pin. Lay trimmed bread slices on counter and cover with a damp towel for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, saute chopped peppers until quite tender. Liberally spread bread slices with cream cheese.
Place a generous helping of green pepper on each slice and roll up.
Place seam side down on a buttered baking sheet.
Brush rolls with melted butter. Bake in the oven at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown, being careful not to burn the underside.
Serve immediately.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan or casserole dish.
Put bell pepper or green chilies on top.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, allspice and cinnamon good.
In another bowl, whip butter.
Add sugar mixture, blending well.
Then add eggs, mixing well after each.
Stir in raisins, nuts and coconut. Pour into two pie crusts and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Sprinkle crushed corn flakes and 1/2 stick butter on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: barbara's best rhubarb pie
directions: Mix rhubarb, strawberries and egg and set aside.
Mix sugar, flour and salt; add to fruit and put into pie crust.
Cover with second pie crust.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top of crust. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oats in boiling water and let cool.
Cream shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg together. Alternate the adding of oats mixture, shortening and sugar.
Baked in an 11 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cut carrots 1/2-inch thick. Cook until tender. Cool. Add onions and pepper. Mix together soup, oil, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Let stand overnight. Will keep 2 weeks.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Mix together well in a large bowl.
Place in loaf pan lined with aluminum foil and chill for several hours.

title: english summer pudding
directions: Arrange 3/4 of cake slices on bottom and sides of an 8 cup souffle dish overlapping or cutting pieces to fit and cover completely.
Set aside.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Line the bottom of a buttered, large glass casserole dish with the rolls, firmly pressing the perforations to seal. Sprinkle with sausage and cheese. Combine remaining ingredients; beat well and pour over sausage and cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set. Let stand 5 minutes. Cut into squares and serve immediately.

title: italian bass stew
directions: Cut
fillets
into
2-inch squares.
Rinse and pat dry. Heat oil in 12-inch Dutch oven over medium heat. Add onion and garlic and cook until soft.
Add
fish, stewed tomatoes, wine, salt, pepper, carrots, mushrooms,
green	pepper,
celery
and potatoes. Cover and cook for 25 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine hamburger, sausage, onion and cooked rice with salt, pepper and egg.
Mix and set aside.
Put can of tomato juice in large kettle and heat.
Boil cabbage in water until leaves are easy to separate.
Peel each leaf and fill with meat mixture. Place into tomato juice and boil 45 to 60 minutes.
(Toothpicks keep the cabbage around the meat mixture.)

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Stir in margarine, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and beaten egg until thoroughly combined.
Spread evenly.
Brown ground chuck with onion and green pepper.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti layer.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top and bake until cheese is melted, approximately 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: mexican snack squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Place crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; press over bottom and 1-inch up sides to form crust. Firmly press perforations to seal. Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely.

title: white grape salad
directions: Heat fruit cocktail until almost boiling. Add sugar and stir until dissolved. Pour over Jello and stir until dissolved. Add pineapple, juice and all.
Add white grape drink last. Refrigerate until completely set.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Bake in loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: purple hull pea jelly
directions: Wash pea hulls thoroughly.
Boil in water until juice is purple-red. Strain juice; measure juice into 8 to 10-quart saucepan.
Add Sure-Jell.
Bring to a boil.
Add all of sugar at one time; stir until sugar dissolves.
Return to a rolling boil. Cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; skim off foam.
Pour into sterilized jars.

title: nacho snacks
directions: Place Doritos in plate.
Put pepperoni on top of each Dorito. Put cheese on top of pepperoni.
Microwave for a few seconds on High.
Great snack!

title: katie's cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients together and form into a ball. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: apple pumpkin desserts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spoon apple filling into 8 to 10 custard cups.
In large bowl, beat pumpkin, sweetened condensed milk, eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Spoon over apple filling. Combine crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over pumpkin.
Place cups on 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 15 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: awesome corn chowder
directions: In a big kettle, fry bacon until crispy. Remove from pan. Cook onions in grease from bacon. Parboil potatoes in a smaller pan. After onions are clear, add milk, corn and cooked potatoes. Warm on low temperature until hot. Stir frequently since corn and potatoes tend to stick. Add bacon when hot or if you have vegetarian friends, serve the bacon in a bowl as a condiment. Eat and enjoy!

title: spinach square
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan, melt butter in 300° oven. In a bowl, beat eggs; add flour, milk, salt and baking powder. Mix well.
Bake 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool 45 minutes. To serve, cut into bite-size pieces.

title: fried shrimp balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form in small balls.
Fry in deep fryer at 375° until golden brown.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into a 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 16.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup and pepper until well blended.
Then mix with potatoes, onion and cheese.
Press into large casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch pan and top with mixed butter and crackers.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
tags: frozen Southern style hash brown potatoes

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding chocolate chips last.
Bake in greased bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool 10-15 mins. before turning out.

title: taco salad
directions: Fix taco seasoning and beef as directed on package.
Combine all ingredients in desired amounts in a Ziploc bag and shake. Pour out into a large bowl and serve.
Taco sauce is optional.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Boil chicken until done, approximately 30 minutes.
Drain and cut into chunks.
In large pan combine soup, water, mustard and salt.
Heat to boiling, add chicken, broccoli and mushrooms.
Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add more water if too thick.
Pour mixture over biscuits or rolls.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: sock-it-to-me-cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except
brown sugar and cinnamon. Pour one-half
of batter in pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over batter.
Pour rest of batter in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tres la leche cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix per directions on box in a 9 x 13 cake pan. After it is cooled poke holes all over it with a toothpick or fork. Mix all three milks together and pour over cake. Let soak in well. Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: frosted orange creme(like orange juice)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; blend well.
Enjoy!

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook
rice
and set aside.
Mix sugar, pineapple, milk, cornstarch, salt, butter, vanilla and egg yolks and cook until thickened.
If
too
thick
add
a little milk or butter.
Add rice
and
mix well.
Pour into dish and sprinkle with nutmeg. Use the egg whites to make meringue for topping.
Brown.

title: buttery strawberry sauce
directions: Cook sugars and water until dissolved. Add butter and cook until melted. Add sliced berries and stir until berries are coated, but not cooked.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together at one time (no need to sift). Use either 13 x 9-inch oblong pan or two 8-inch round pans. Grease and flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Cook chicken and cut into pieces.
Stir-fry veggies (Japanese Birds Eye).
Add 3/4 cup water and bouillon.
Add chicken.
Can be thickened, if you wish.
Serve over rice.

title: spinach ricotta pie
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Squeeze out liquid.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Stir in spinach, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
In a large bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, half and half, Parmesan and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in spinach mixture. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 minutes, or until custard is set and top is lightly browned.

title: lilian's lemon meat balls
directions: Put vegeburger in bowl.
In a separate bowl, put bread crumbs with ketchup and slightly beaten egg.
Mix well.
Add to vegeburger.
Then add cheese, pepper, onion, lemon juice and salt. Mix well.
Shape into 12 balls.
Sprinkle with baco chips.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Turn once during baking.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: You will need wooden toothpicks.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until mushy; drain. Add all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and a small amount of butter. Mix well. Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with reserved cheese, cracker crumbs and melted margarine. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buttery tart shells(makes 2.)
directions: Blend flour and salt in a medium bowl.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut butter into flour until mixture resembles cornmeal. Sprinkle with ice water and quickly mix with a fork until dough lumps together.
Press together and divide in half.
Shape each half into a ball; pat out on a floured surface.
Roll out to a 7 inch circle.
Fit each circle into a 4 inch tart pan.
Trim pastry 1/2 inch from rim.
Moisten underside of overhanging pastry and fold under to make double thickness.
Crimp edge of crust with fork tines or fingers.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until transparent (do not brown). Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add some water if needed.
For serving, you can top this with ripe olives, sliced crumbled bacon, or grated Parmesan.
Delicious hot, but also good cold.

title: country crust bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs, 1/4 cup oil and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in size (about 1 hour).
Punch down and divide in half.
Roll each half into an 18 x 9-inch rectangle. Roll each half up tightly.
Place loaves seam side down into 9 x 5 x 2-inch greased baking pans.
Brush with oil.
Let rise (about 1 hour).
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake until loaves are golden brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: crunchy cheeseroni
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese and onion rings.
Place half the mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 the cheese and onion rings.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday mint pie
directions: Mix cookies and hot water; spoon over crust.
Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually add sugar, milk and peppermint extract.
Fold in whipped topping.
Divide mixture in half.
Add green food coloring to half.
Fill pie crust, alternating dollops of white and green whip.
Smooth with spatula.
Chill for 3 hours.
Top with spearmint leaves and candies.

title: dana's great green peppers
directions: Cook meat, peppers and onion until veggies are tender.
Drain grease.
Add canned tomatoes (do not drain).
Add uncooked rice, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Keep pan covered with a lid.
Shut heat off.
Cut Velveeta up into cubes.
Add cheese to mixture. Cover and let sit for approximately 10 minutes; stir.

title: easy tuna melt(yields 2 servings)
directions: Combine tuna, salad dressing and dill pickle relish.
Top 2 toasted English muffin halves with a tomato slice, half the tuna mix and a slice of cheese.
Broil or microwave until cheese begins to melt.

title: diabetic chocolate brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over hot water.
Remove from heat. Add sugar and beaten egg and mix well.
Add vanilla, flour and salt.
Pour into greased pan and bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pita bread(makes 12)
directions: Heat water
and
oil
until hot to touch (125° - 150°). Add sugar and
yeast.
Set
aside
for 5 minutes.
Set aside 1 cup flour.
Mix
remaining
flour and salt into yeast mixture. Stir in remaining
flour
to
make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic
(8 to 10 minutes).
Cover, let rise for 10 minutes. Divide
dough
into
smooth
balls.
Let rise 30 minutes.
On a lightly floured surface roll each ball into a 5 inch circle. Place
circles
on a large cooling rack.
Set rack on bottom level of oven rack;
bake at 500° for 5 minutes or until
puffed and
the top begins to brown.
Cool.
Repeat with remaining circles.

title: fast fumi salad
directions: Heat margarine; stir in seasoning packet from noodles.
Break block of noodles into bite size over skillet.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add sesame seed.
Cook and stir 2 minutes longer, until noodles are golden brown.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil and pepper in a large bowl.
Add noodle mixture and remaining ingredients.
Toss. Serves 6.

title: cauliflower salad bowl
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets; slice thin crosswise. Add tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.
Pour Italian dressing over top; toss lightly.

title: no peeking dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine egg whites, cream of tartar, vanilla and salt.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in oven.
Turn oven off.
Leave overnight (no peeking).

title: macaroni and cheese(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine macaroni, flour, onion and salt. Stir in milk and water.
Cook on High, covered, 10 to 12 minutes or until almost tender.
Stir in cheese.
Cook 2 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes to finish cooking.
Use at least a 2-quart casserole or it will boil over.

title: pink pasta sauce
directions: Place butter into small saucepan and allow to melt over medium-low heat.
Add flour and stir until combined.
Slowly add milk, constantly stirring, until all milk is added and mixture becomes thick.
Slowly add canned pasta sauce and continue cooking until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat and pour (or spoon) over prepared pasta.
Makes a great side dish.

title: icing(for decorating cakes)
directions: Mix Crisco, Dream Whip and vanilla on high speed for 5 minutes.
Add powdered sugar, milk and flour.
Mix for an additional 2 to 3 minutes.
This can be cut in half if desired.

title: corn chowder
directions: Place potatoes in a Dutch oven or kettle, cover with water and cook until tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes or until the onion is soft.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, with fork, beat cream cheese until smooth. Add pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Mix thoroughly and shape into ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic film or foil.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.
Can be rewrapped and frozen.

title: mary's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in loaf pan for about 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
When done, drain excess fat off.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt oleo.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in pan and mix with oleo.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Refrigerate leftover portion.
Very good.

title: stupid pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix nuts, crackers, sugar and vanilla.
Then add to egg whites; pour into greased pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
The longer this pie sets, the better it gets.

title: rosy glow punch
directions: Make
ice
cubes and freeze solid.
Combine the juices. Pour over
apple juice ice cubes in tall glasses, filling 1/3 full. Fill
to
top with carbonated beverage.
Stir gently to mix. Makes 12 servings.

title: chex party mix
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add to cereal, peanuts and pretzel sticks. Mix until coated.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and milk in saucepan and cook until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter,
butter
and
vanilla.
Beat until cool.
Pour into buttered pan or dish.
When cold, cut into squares.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add the rest at once.
Put rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: snowball pate
directions: Mash liver sausage with a fork.
Blend in lemon juice, onion and mayonnaise.
Pack into a small bowl.
Cover with foil.
Chill at least 2 hours or until firm.
Soften cream cheese.
Slowly blend in milk until mixture is easy to spread.
Frost with cream cheese.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and buttermilk well.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Add hot shortening.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients; beat egg until light.
Add fruit cocktail.
Mix and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Before baking, mix nuts and brown sugar and sprinkle over top of cake mixture. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: banana loaf
directions: Mix together like cake; add mashed bananas, orange peel and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then lower to 225° for 45 minutes.

title: black olive dip
directions: Mix shrimp soup and cream cheese together over low heat until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat but do not boil.
Serve in chafing dish.
Use corn chips for dipping.

title: thrifty pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix together Crisco, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Add 1 cup buttermilk with flour mixture.
Bake in tube pan or 3 layer pans at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Boil water and sugar together; add flour paste and cook 5 minutes. Mix the yolks of eggs, lemon juice, rind and salt. Add 1 tablespoon of hot sugar mixture to yolk mixture and stir. Repeat 3 times. Add this mixture to the remainder of the sugar mixture. Cool slightly. Fluff 1/2 of egg whites until stiff. Add to sugar mixture. Pour into previously baked crust. Make a meringue of the remaining egg whites by beating whites until stiff. Add 2 tablespoons sugar. Cover pie with meringue. Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach; squeeze dry.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl with spinach.
Cover; chill for 2 hours. Form into 1-inch balls.
(May be frozen at this point.)
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 300° oven.
Makes about 2 1/2 to 3 dozen balls.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine salad oil, water, eggs and pumpkin.
Stir until well blended.
In plastic bag, combine raisins, pecans and 2 tablespoons flour.
Shake until well coated; set aside.
Combine 3 1/3 cups flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add liquid ingredients and stir well.
Stir in raisin mixture.

title: cheese balls
directions: Save 1 cup pecans to roll cheese ball.
Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Will be soft.
Shape into balls.
Coat with pecans. Refrigerate if not serving right away! Makes 2 cheese balls.

title: impossible lasagne pie
directions: Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes in 10 x 1 1/2-inch greased pie plate.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli.
Remove tough ends of lower stalks and wash broccoli.
Separate flowerets and coarsely chop stalks.
Bring water to a boil.
Add salt and broccoli.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until crisp and tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: crab puffs(makes approximately 90 pieces)
directions: Melt butter or margarine and mix together first five ingredients.
Spread mixture onto English muffins, then cut into quarters.
Place quarters on cookie sheet and freeze.
If you don't freeze them first, they will be too soft when baked and topping will run off before browning.

title: apple chutney(servings:  4)
directions: Cut peppers into halves and remove seeds.
Pare apples and remove core.
Force vegetables, apples, ginger and raisins through a food processor.
Combine all ingredients and cook until thick and clear, about 1 hour.
Fill sterile jars and seal.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: vegetable saute
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high.
Add vegetables. Cook-stir until tender-crisp.
Sprinkle salad dressing over vegetables.
Toss to coat.
Stir in vinegar.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding powders together; add Cool Whip and La Creme. Add all other ingredients and chill until ready to use.

title: husband's delight
directions: Use 8 x 12-inch or 10-inch baking dish.
Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Spread in bottom of dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, until light brown.
Let cool.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Prepare 1 pie crust in a quiche pan.
Prick bottom and bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 450° oven.
Keep oven hot.
Put half the spinach, 1/2 the Swiss and 1/2 the onions in the pie shell, then top with the other half.
Make a mix of Parmesan cheese, eggs, half and half and Worcestershire plus 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Mix and pour over spinach-cheese arrangement.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° and then at 325° for 25 minutes or until firm.

title: mala's chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts with quartered orange and quartered onion. Salt and pepper water to taste.
Meanwhile, chop green onions. Drain oranges and combine in bowl with nuts and mayo.
(Begin with 1/2 cup; add more when chicken is added.)
Remove chicken.
Cool and chop into bite-sized pieces.
Add to mayo mixture.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put shredded cabbage in slow cooker after mixing with onion soup mix and French dressing.
Cook until cabbage is done.

title: super seafood dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with pita or bagel chips.
Yields 2 3/4 cups.

title: peggy's punch
directions: Combine juices, sugar and mint; chill. Just before serving, add the remaining ingredients. Makes 75 four-ounce servings.

title: hungarian noodles and cabbage(galooshka)
directions: Add enough olive oil to coat the bottom of a nonstick skillet. Heat oil, add cabbage, onion, salt and pepper; saute until cabbage is browned.
Cook, rinse and drain noodles.
Return noodles to pan they were cooked in.
Add cabbage mixture and stir until completely mixed.

title: grandma griffin's egg custard
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Scald butter and milk.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add scalded milk and butter to egg mixture slowly.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put in oven and reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash with 2 tablespoons each of melted butter and brown sugar.
Add mustard and egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix corn flakes, remaining butter and brown sugar.
Sprinkle over top of squash.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Put in 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch Pyrex casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or longer.
Check to make sure center is firm.

title: sugar free fruit cake
directions: Put first four ingredients together and bring to boil, then simmer 5 minutes.
Take off heat and mash.
Add margarine and vanilla; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well, pour in 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Adjust baking time for high altitude.

title: low-fat turkey and baked beans
directions: Brown turkey in a skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Add onions and green pepper; mix well.
Cook until vegetables are tender, stirring constantly; drain.
Add catsup, pork and beans, pinto beans, brown sugar, molasses, liquid smoke and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.

title: special chicken and rice
directions: Prepare Minute Rice as directed, keep warm.
Meanwhile, cook peppers in oil in covered skillet over low heat until tender, but not browned, also the onions at the same time.
Blend cornstarch with a small amount of chicken stock.
Add remaining stock and soy sauce and cornstarch mixture to vegetables.
Add chicken and cook until sauce is clear and thickened.
Add tomatoes and cook.
Just to heat.
Serve on rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, milk and egg until blended. Beat until smooth. Add salt and pepper.
Put pie plate on top shelf (allowing 4-inch clearance for pudding to rise).
Pour drippings into glass pie plate.
Pour batter into pie plate slowly.
Push in rack slowly.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes or until pudding has risen and has lightly browned.
Serve with roast beef and top with gravy.
Serves 4.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together in a skillet and let simmer for a few minutes.
Drain off fat.
Then add other ingredients and let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: german fried potatoes
directions: Grate potatoes; add onion and egg.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Spoon in hot grease to form patties.
Fry. Turn when brown.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix together flour, butter and chopped nuts; pat into 9 x 13-inch
pan
for
crust.
Bake
in
oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let
cool.
Cream together cream cheese, soften with powdered
sugar and spread on cooled crust.
Mix instant lemon pudding
in
milk,	mixing	well until thickened.
Spread over cream
cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip (mixed with instant vanilla
pudding
if
it's	to sit out awhile).
Sprinkle with nuts, cut, serve and enjoy!

title: banana loaf cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine; add sugar, then the beaten egg.
Add soda, salt and baking powder into sifted flour.
Then combine all ingredients and bake in loaf pan or bread pan in 350° oven for about 35 minutes.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.

title: seaside shrimp casserole
directions: Clean fish and wipe off excess water.
Cut into serving pieces or cubes; set aside.
Saute onion in butter until soft but not browned.
Add garlic and fish to onions; heat to simmer.
Cook for 10 to 20 minutes until fish is just tender and flakes easily. Don't overcook.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; set aside.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, spices and salt; set aside. Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Combine boiling water and molasses.
Stir in soda until dissolved and add to batter.
Gradually add flour mixture, stirring well between each addition.
Pour into a well-greased 8-inch square pan or 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan until gingerbread shrinks away from sides and then invert onto rack and cool completely.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Skin chicken, combine all ingredients and marinate chicken for as little as 15 minutes to as much as overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: seafood tartlets
directions: Roll each bread slice to 1/4-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2-inch daisy shaped cutter.
Lightly brush each side with butter and gently press into miniature muffin tins.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Rinse shrimp.
Let stand in ice water 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine shrimp and next 5 ingredients.
Stir well.
Spoon mixture into shells and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Garnish with paprika and parsley flakes.
Yields about 2 dozen appetizers.

title: cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese and eggs set at room temperature.
Cream cheese, sugar and eggs (adding eggs, one at a time and beating after each one).
Add vanilla.
Pour this mixture into a well buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan that has been lightly dusted with graham cracker crumbs.
Bake for 50 minutes at 300°.
Do not overbake.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve the strawberry jello into boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and let thaw in mixture. Add the crushed pineapple and chopped nuts.
Pour half of the mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan. Chill until firm. Add sour cream.
Add remaining strawberry mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt and basil.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Set sauce aside.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Tie spice in cheesecloth bag.
Put all in pan and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with a twist of orange peel or apple slice and a stick of cinnamon.

title: angel hair pasta with lemon and garlic
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat and maintain at a boil.
Put the olive oil and garlic in a saute pan and cook over medium heat just until the garlic begins to brown. Remove the saute pan from the heat and pour in the wine.
Return it to the heat.
Cook for another 1 to 2 minutes, until the wine has been reduced by half.
Stir in the lemon juice and tomato. Remove the pan from the heat.

title: spiced cider
directions: Mix ingredients and heat thoroughly until candy melts.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients and microwave until hot.
Dip chips into mixture and enjoy.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook the water, syrup and salt to hard ball stage when tested in a cup of cool water.
Stir frequently.
Beat the egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Pour cooked mixture into egg whites in a very slow stream, continuing to beat while you pour.
(If you pour cooked mixture all at once, the egg whites will curdle.)
Continue to beat until thickened.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat 1 more minute.
Pour immediately into buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix for 3 minutes.
Spread mixture in a well-greased loaf pan.
