Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add Fritos and dressing just before serving.

title: crunchy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve and cool jello add the rest of mixture to the dissolved jello and mix well. Put in a sprayed
pan. Cover and chill.

title: edna's butter mints
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Gradually add sugar.
Shape into balls; dip a fork into additional sugar and flatten.
Dry 8 to 10 hours on waxed paper before storing in an airtight tin.
Paste food coloring can be used to tint the mints any color desired.
Do not use liquid food coloring, as mints will not set.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar.
Mix flour and butter.
Then add all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for another 30 to 35 minutes.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add 6 tablespoons sugar. Spread over pies and brown.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Melt margarine or butter in microwave casserole dish one minute at 100% power.
Separate onion slices into rings.
Toss potatoes and onion in melted margarine or butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and stir well.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes, stirring halfway through. Let stand and set, covered, for 3 minutes and serve.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Freeze in 2 containers.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a saucepan, saute margarine and onions.
Add milk and mushroom soup. Bring to a boil and add stuffing mix. Add cooked, mashed squash. Put into a casserole dish. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked bean delight
directions: Bring apple juice and water to a boil.
Add beans and cook until almost tender, about 2 hours.
Drain beans, saving liquid, and add all other ingredients except vegetables.
Cover and bake in a 250° oven for 2 to 3 hours.
Uncover for last 1/2 hour of baking and add tomato or green pepper.
If beans get dry, add some of the bean liquid.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, flour and eggs.
Add milk, water, vanilla and coconut.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: ham-cheese-egg bake
directions: Coat 9 x 13-inch baking pan with margarine.
Add 1 1/2 packages crescent rolls in bottom of pan.
Spread ingredients over crescent rolls except eggs and milk.
Beat eggs and add to milk. Pour over mixture.
Break 1/2 package rolls into small pieces. Add on top of mixture.
Bake at 325° for approximately 50 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8.

title: new england style corn chowder
directions: Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Add the onion and saute over low heat until onion is golden color.
Then add the water, carrots, celery and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are tender (about 20 minutes).
Add corn, milk and seasonings.
Continue to heat with occasional stirring, just until chowder reaches boiling point.
Serve hot!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup.
Cook to hard ball stage when tested in cold water.
Add peanuts; cook until syrup is color of shell of peanut.
Remove from fire.
Add butter and baking soda; stir well.
Pour onto buttered trays.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in casserole dish and top with 3 soups, already mixed together.
Place chicken on top of that and dot each piece with butter.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix sugar, salt, pepper, oil, vinegar and celery salt.
Pour this over the chopped vegetables.
The longer it sets, the better it is.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and 1 cup of sugar. Stir in egg and molasses.
Stir in all remaining dry ingredients except 1/2 cup sugar.
Form dough into 1-inch diameter balls and roll in remaining sugar.
Place 2 to 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheets, until firm.
Remove carefully with spatula.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: italian delight(an old family favorite from the 1930's)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion until crumbly.
Add minced garlic. Stir briefly; add tomato sauce, mushrooms, olives and half of the cheese.
Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook spaghetti in boiling water until tender, then drain and rinse.
Remove all water from spaghetti.
Add spaghetti to hamburger mixture; mix well.
Put into baking dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour turnips
directions: Place turnips in a saucepan; cover with water.
Add salt and bring to boil; cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes, or until tender. Drain and set aside.
Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Combine egg, sugar and vinegar in a small mixing bowl, mixing well; stir into bacon and drippings.
Pour bacon mixture over turnips and toss gently.
Yields about 4 servings.

title: peach bundles(method:  foil packet)
directions: Place half of a canned peach on a sheet of aluminum foil.
Put 1 to 2 teaspoons of chocolate chips in center.
On top of chocolate chips, place 2 marshmallows.
Wrap in foil, using drugstore wrap method; be sure to seal tightly.
Bake in coals for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: instant rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan. Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 12 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: "green stuff"
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add jello.
Let pineapple and jello cool almost completely.
Fold in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Pour into jello mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Good for diabetics!

title: parmesan bread slices
directions: Cut French bread into 1/2-inch slices.
Brush both sides of the slices with a hearty bottled Italian dressing.
Sprinkle top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Heat on baking sheet 5 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: pineapple butter
directions: In the blender, put pineapple chunks and apples with just enough pineapple juice to blend them into a thick butter.
Remove from blender and add honey.
Keep in a covered dish in the refrigerator.

title: great grill burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients as you would for meat loaf.
Separate and pat out into six patties.
Grill to desired doneness and serve on buns with your favorite condiments.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop all ingredients together in food processor.
Great with chicken pie or turkey.

title: italian cream for puffs(crema italiano)
directions: From my Aunt Lena.

title: skillet chef's salad
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot olive or salad oil, cook green onions just until tender.
Stir in flour, sugar and salt until smooth. Add vinegar, mustard and 1/2 cup water. Cook, stirring, until dressing boils and thickens slightly.
Remove skillet from heat.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1 cake layer into bottom of punch bowl.
Layer 1/2 of all ingredients on crumbled cake.
Repeat with second layer. Optional:
garnish with sliced bananas (soaked in pineapple juice) and maraschino cherries.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix above ingredients, except for the nuts, together and shape into a ball.
Cover with chopped nuts.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach.
Press out liquid.
Combine spinach, soup, cheese and onion.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Toss stuffing with butter and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces; reserve broth. Combine in large mixing bowl soup, cooked rice, mayonnaise, pimientos, onion, dash of salt and pepper and 1/2 cup of the reserved chicken broth.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mildew killer
directions: Add all ingredients to a gallon container and fill to 1 gallon with water.

title: redenbacher's ribbon o' fudge bars
directions: In a large Dutch oven, over low heat, melt marshmallows with butterscotch chips and butter.
Stir occasionally until smooth. Add popcorn.
Toss until well coated.
Press half of mixture firmly into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread fudge sauce evenly over mixture.
Press remaining popcorn mixture over fudge. Allow mixture to cool and harden.
Slide spatula under entire mixture and slide onto a cutting board to cut into bars.
Makes 16 bars.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add sour cream. Mix flour and soda.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° in a 10-inch greased tube pan.
Mix and put on cake while hot:

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease muffin tins.
Bake at 370° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 24 to 36 muffins.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Herb Dressing.

title: special spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix with tomato soup, spaghetti sauce and mushrooms.
In a 10 x 14 x 2-inch casserole dish, layer the following:
spaghetti, Parmesan, meat mixture and cheeses.
Top with the mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast puffs
directions: Roll dough 1/8 in thickness.
Cut as for biscuits.

title: dill chip dip
directions: Mix all above ingredients well.
Will keep weeks in refrigerator.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Place bread in prepared dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: jello-cheese salad
directions: 1st Layer:
1 head lettuce, chopped in bowl.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix cheeses, egg and spices together until blended.
Cook shells in 2 1/2 quarts salted water.
Drain.
Fill shells with cheese filling.
Cover bottom of baking dish with sauce.
Place layer of stuffed shells, cover with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with more cheese.

title: golden potatoes(microwave recipe)
directions: Make thin crosswise cuts almost through, but not all the way, on 6 medium potatoes.
Arrange in a circle on a 12-inch plate. Drizzle with oleo or butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover tightly and microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Turn potatoes over, brush with oleo and sprinkle with paprika, cover and microwave until tender (about 6 to 8 minutes).

title: pretzel-crusted chicken
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add pretzels and next 3 ingredients.
Process until pretzels resemble fine crumbs. Place in a large, heavy-duty, Zip-top plastic bag; set aside. Combine flour and next 4 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir in beer and egg.
Dip chicken pieces, one at a time, in batter; place in bag of pretzel mixture, shaking to coat.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Yield:
4 servings.

title: rabbit in apple cider
directions: In Dutch oven, melt butter in oil over medium-low heat.
Add rabbit; brown well on all sides over medium-high heat.
Remove rabbit; set aside.
Add onion and carrots to oil.
Cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Stir in cider, salt, thyme, bay leaf and peppercorns.
Heat to boiling.
Add browned rabbit. Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer until rabbit pieces are tender, 50 to 60 minutes.
Core and quarter apples.
Add to rabbit.
Recover. Simmer until apples are just tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Discard bay leaf and serve.

title: salmon and creamettes
directions: Cook Creamettes in salted water; drain and place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add flaked salmon, salt and pepper.
Pour sour cream and melted butter over casserole.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine.
Roll breast in margarine and then in bread crumb mixture.
Place 1 tablespoon oil in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place coated breast in pan; pour 1/3 cup water over breast.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup wine; bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: salmon pate
directions: Blend all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Line a small bowl with Saran wrap and fill.
Keep it refrigerated overnight.	Turn out on a flat plate and remove Saran wrap. Sprinkle with nuts or parsley or paprika; olives are pretty on top also.
Place crackers around plate before serving.

title: surprise muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease the bottoms of 18 muffin cups or line with baking cups.
Beat egg, milk and oil in medium bowl with fork until blended.
Mix flour and sugar to egg mixture and stir until moistened (will look lumpy).
Spoon batter into muffin cups, filling each cup 1/3 full.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon of jelly onto the center of each and top with enough batter to fill 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Mix eggs, milk, flour and seasonings.
Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain and place in 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour flour mixture over this and bake at 425° for 24 to 25 minutes. Remove.
Drizzle pizza sauce on top and add cheese.
Return and heat until cheeses are melted.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons pancake flour and ginger; coat chicken pieces.
Fry in skillet until brown.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Add to it rest of pancake mix.
Cover in tightly covered container and shake.
Stir mixture with vinegar, soy sauce and Worcestershire into fat in skillet.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Reduce heat.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and chicken.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add pineapple and green pepper.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes more.
Stir in water chestnuts, bean sprouts and chili sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Tie cinnamon sticks, allspice and cloves in a cheesecloth bag. Combine spices, cider, pineapple juice and sugar in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice; cook over low heat 10 minutes or just until heated.
Remove spice bag.
Pour into cups and garnish each with a cinnamon stick. Yields 11 cups.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown meat and onion in pan.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes. Season with garlic powder, onion powder, etc.
Add rice and mix. Stuff peppers and put any remaining mixture in bottom of pan. Bake approximately 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shortbread
directions: Combine butter and sugar; blend well, being careful not to let butter get too soft.
(Best to mix with hands.) Gradually blend in flour; mix well.
Pat and press in 9 x 13-inch jelly roll pan. Prick with fork.
Put in fridge for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes, then at 300° for 30 minutes, or until light brown. (Watch closely; don't let it get too brown.)
Remove from oven; cut into squares.
Sprinkle with white sugar.
Store in tin, not in Tupperware!

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all together and pour into a hot, oiled griddle or skillet.
Cook until top is full of holes, then turn pancake over and cook over a little longer.
Serve with your favorite toppings.

title: diabetic date coffee cake
directions: Beat together mashed bananas and butter until creamy.
Add eggs, vanilla and water and beat.
Add flour, baking soda and baking powder; mix well.
Stir in dates, walnuts and coconut. Spoon into an oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add pie filling and pineapple. Refrigerate & serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix with other ingredients.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with Hawaiian bread or French bread.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute 1/2 cup onions in 3 tablespoons butter until soft.
Cook 2 packages broccoli according to package directions.
Add 1 cup Minute rice and 1 cup water to onions and simmer 5 minutes, covered.
Add celery soup, 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz. Mix good and pour into 2-quart dish and bake in 350° oven until slightly brown on top.

title: fruitcake squares
directions: Pour melted margarine in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Sprinkle evenly with wafer crumbs.
Arrange cherries, pineapple, dates and pecans evenly over the crumbs.
Press down gently. Combine milk and vanilla.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil milk and sugar for 6 minutes in large kettle.
Pour this hot mixture over the other ingredients and stir until melted. Pour into foil-lined cookie sheet to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all together.
Make small balls (teaspoonful).
Should make about 65 to 75 balls.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add onion and green pepper.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Pour mixture into pan.
Put seasoned chicken on top, skin side down and cover. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: mayonnaise biscuits or muffins
directions: Stir ingredients together until smooth.
Drop from spoon into 6 greased muffin tins.
Bake in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: easy lemon chicken
directions: In a skillet brown chicken in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil. Pour off fat.
Add gravy, lemon, thyme and vegetables.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until done.
Spoon into pastry shells.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate mint sticks
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and 2 squares chocolate together; cool. Beat eggs; gradually add sugar.
Beat well.
Add cooled chocolate mixture, vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon peppermint extract. Mix in flour.
By hand, stir in nuts.
Spread batter into greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: wine biscuits
directions: In a blender, add chocolate chips, egg, sugar, vanilla and rum.
Heat milk to almost scalding.
Add milk to blender.
Blend 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into pot de creme cups or other small containers.
Refrigerate 6 hours.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: left-over turkey
directions: Mix everything but the chips.
Stir well.
Butter casserole dish.
Pour some of the mixture in the bottom of the pan.
Layer with chips.
Repeat meat, chips; meat, chips.
You can shred the cheese or grate it over each layer or just put it over the top. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and cheese melts.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stir all together and bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove chicken from bone and bring broth to boiling.
Add cream of chicken soup and dumplings.
Mash down but do not stir, except to separate.
Cook until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut off stove and let set.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple tart
directions: Beat butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat in egg and salt.
Gradually add flour to make a soft dough.
Cover tightly. Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Roll dough on floured surface to make 10-inch circle.
Place in glass quiche pan or round tart pan.

title: foolproof pie crust(makes 6)
directions: In a bowl, mix first four ingredients.
In a separate bowl, combine vinegar, egg and cold water.
Combine the two mixes and chill at least 15 minutes before rolling out.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and pecans in a jar to coat well.
Spread out in a shallow pan.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Add butter and salt and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Cut fryer in quarters.
In a skillet, saute chicken in heated oil until skin is golden.
Remove chicken and place in a casserole.
In the same olive oil, saute onions, green pepper, tomatoes and garlic for 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken and add chicken broth, saffron and rice.
When it begins to boil, cover casserole and bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Sprinkle with wine and garnish with peas, pimientos and asparagus tips.
Serves 4.

title: green goddess vegetable dip
directions: Mix in blender. Chill well. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: pot pie noodles
directions: Mix all together and roll.
Cut into squares; drop into boiling stew.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix onion, oil, honey, ketchup, soy sauce, and mustard in a plastic or glass bowl (don't use a metal one). Put chicken in and make sure thoroughly coated with the marinade. Leave to marinate for either 1 1/2 hours in the fridge, or for 45 minutes at room temperature. Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix flour, oleo and milk.
Pour half into greased medium sized baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour into crust.
Pour rest of crust on top.
Bake 1 hour at 400° or until brown.

title: punch
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: very best pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco together.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Add baking powder to flour. Alternate flour and milk, mixing well.
Add flavorings last.
This will make a large cake.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: earthquake dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add enough shredded coconut to cover bottom.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over coconut.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour over coconut and nut layer.
Combine margarine, sugar and softened cream cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Spoon over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until done.
Serve with a scoop of vanilla ice cream and enjoy!

title: orange salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Add hot liquid. Mix. Cook over low heat until bubbly, stirring constantly. Cool. Fold in Dream Whip and oranges. Chill. Serves 9 to 10.

title: burnt almond coffee(servings:  8)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toast almonds on a baking sheet until they are a rich deep brown.
Remove from the oven and cool. Combine almonds and coffee beans and grind together.
Prepare ground mixture with 1 quart of water as you would any other coffee.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Bring sugar and pineapple to boil.
Add jello and warm water and refrigerate until cool.
Add whipping cream and nuts. Refrigerate until jelled.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook the sugar, milk, Karo syrup and peanuts on low fire for 1 hour, or until mixture forms a semi-firm ball when dropped into cold water.
Stir real often.
Add the butter, vanilla and food coloring.
Beat for 3 or 4 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Yields about 35 patties.

title: homestyle cornbread
directions: Sift flour, cornmeal, baking powder, soda and salt together in mixing bowl.
Combine sugar and egg; beat until light.
Add sour milk or buttermilk and shortening.
Combine slowly with dry ingredients.
If milk is quite thick, a little more may be needed to thin batter.
Stir only until mixed.
Grease pan (9 x 13-inch) generously; cover with thick sprinkling of cornmeal.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for about 25 minutes, or until nicely browned.

title: no fail-pie crust
directions: Place in medium size Tupperware bowl.
Put seal on bowl and shake briskly.
Then add 1/2 cup water.
Replace seal and shake again.
Dough will need very little, if any, handling

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix sour cream, dry mustard, pepper, salt, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend 2 minutes at low speed.
Add mayonnaise.
Blend 1/2 minute at low speed, then 2 minutes at medium speed.
Crumble by hand the cheese into small pieces and add.
Blend at low speed no longer than 4 minutes.

title: glorified rice
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Whip cream and fold in all ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine and bring to boil for 3 minutes Jell-O and crushed pineapple; let cool.
Add cottage cheese, marshmallows, nuts, diced apples and Cool Whip.
Chill.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: cherry crumb dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, cut butter into cake mix as for pastry dough.
Set aside 1 cup.
Pat remaining crumbs onto the bottom and 1/2 inch up the sides of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Spread pie filling over crust.
Combine the walnuts with reserved crumbs; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream if desired.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: whipped cream topping jello salad
directions: Use method suggested on Jell-O package for setting.

title: no bake mini cheesecake
directions: Mix cheesecake crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press onto bottoms of each of 12 paper or foil lined muffin cups with spoon or bottom of glass.
Beat on medium for 3 minutes.
Filling will be thick.
Spoon over crumb mixture in muffin cups.
Refrigerate.

title: sesame bars
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Add sesame seed and coconut.
Mix well.
Dip hands in water, then press ingredients into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Yield:
30 (2-inch) bars.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Slice eggs on top.
Pour in broth and soup.
Mix flour, milk and butter together. Stir well.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eight layer dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.

In large cake pan, layer above ingredients in order: beans avocado dip, sour cream mixture, chopped olives, chopped green chilies, chopped green onions, chopped tomatoes and grated Cheddar cheese. Serve with corn flavored tortilla chips for dipping.

title: beer cheese dip
directions: Place all ingredients except crackers into a bowl of the food processor and process until pureed and fully combined.
Spoon into the crock and chill.
Serve on platter surrounded by assorted crackers.

title: special cheese ring
directions: Mix with hands and mold into desired shape (a ring or a ball). If using ring
shape, center can be filled with strawberry jam. Place in refrigerator until chilled.

title: strawberry shortcake cake
directions: Grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows in pan.
Combine thawed strawberries and syrup with dry gelatin. Set aside.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except half the cheese.
Turn into casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: waffles or pancakes #2
directions: I use 6 tablespoons melted butter instead of oil.

title: party pick ups
directions: Cream together the butter and cheese; add pepper, flour and salt.
Knead well.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and pie filling.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until done.
Frosting with Chocolate Frosting for Cherry Chocolate Cake.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until tender with bay leaves and small onion and salt.
Cool and cut in pieces.
Simmer in fat of hen for one hour the large onion, bell pepper, celery and tomatoes.
Add ripe olives, mushrooms and pimento.
Cook 9 ounces spaghetti in salted chicken broth.
Drain.
Mix together chicken, sauce and spaghetti. Put on serving dish, topping with grated cheese.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two loaf pans.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add bananas and eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt. Add to mixture.
Do not overmix.
Bake in loaf pans 45 to 50 minutes.
You may add 1 cup walnuts if desired.
This recipe makes an unbelievably moist, delicious banana bread.

title: greek boiled shrimp
directions: Brush shrimp with oil and broil for 3 minutes.
Mix olive oil and lemon juice and pour over broiled shrimp.
Serve.

title: perfect peanut butter pie 'n' crust
directions: Mix the powdered sugar and peanut butter (I prefer Jif) until it resembles "Bisquick".
Spread almost 3/4 of the mixture on the baked, cooled pie shell crust.

title: pickles
directions: Drain liquid from dill pickles; rinse and drain.
If whole, cut in strips and put back in can.
Mix sugar and seasonings. Pour over pickles.
Let stand at least 24 hours.
Shake frequently to dissolve sugar.

title: skillet chicken and sausage
directions: In a large skillet, fry sausage until brown and well cooked; remove and cut into 1/2-inch rounds.

Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and brown on all sides in sausage drippings; remove. Add rice to drippings and cook until brown, stirring constantly. Add chicken, sausage, chicken broth and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice and chicken are tender.
Stir in peas, mushrooms and pimiento; cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until peas are tender.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Stir until mixed well.
Add nutmeats and chips.
Blend.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dressing casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs, margarine and 4 cups broth. Put 2 cups bread crumbs in bottom of baking dish. Add chicken mixture. Add 2 more cups bread crumbs. Melt margarine and add 4 cups broth. Pour on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage salad dressing
directions: Pour ingredients into shaker; shake well.
Pour over cabbage, mix.

title: chow mein fudge
directions: Melt bits in double boiler.
Add chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat firmly and bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: onion rings
directions: Soak onions in ice water for 2 hours.
Make batter of remaining ingredients.
Dip onions in batter.
Deep fry until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese with mixer.
Add Cheddar cheese and next 7 ingredients; beat until creamy.
Stir in parsley and pimento. Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: frozen dessert
directions: In a double boiler, melt the butter.
Add 2 cups powdered sugar and 3 well beaten eggs; mix well and cook 4 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put a layer of vanilla wafer crumbs, a layer of cooled filling, a layer of pineapple, next the nuts, then the whipped cream.
Top with vanilla wafer crumbs and freeze.

title: cherry bars
directions: Beat soft oleo, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Then add flour. Spread 2/3 of dough into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over dough.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Stir together the baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms. Beat 30 seconds. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Combine butter and garlic; brush on biscuits. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on each biscuit. Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix the filling ingredients in the order given and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix margarine, flour, nuts and graham crackers.
Press into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat until thick powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Then add Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pan.
Stir together instant pudding and milk; pour over top.
Cover the top with remaining Cool Whip. Sprinkle nuts on top and refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Divide the apple slices between four 10 ounce custard cups.
Sprinkle water over apple slices.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat about 1-inch of oil in a skillet to 375°.
Beat eggs well in a large mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until batter is smooth.
Holding opening of funnel covered with finger, pour 1/4 cup batter into a wide mouth funnel.

When ready to fry, release finger and run batter into hot oil using a slow, wide, circular motion and maintaining as steady a stream as possible. Fry, turning once, until golden brown, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Repeat until all batter is used. Sprinkle generously with confectioners sugar.
Best served warm. Makes 10 large.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Stir together all but popcorn and cook to medium heat until it boils.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour over popped corn.
Bake at 250° for one hour; stir every 15 minutes.
Turn out on brown paper bag until cool.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, dill, garlic, salt and pepper in medium saucepan.
After bringing to a boil, lower heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Peel cucumbers and slice thin pieces into a non-corrosive bowl.
Pour marinade over cucumbers and refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Drain and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: salad!
directions: Mix, chop and etc. ingredients as desired.
Cook anything that might need to be cooked.
Cheerfully serve with love.

title: overnight dinner rolls
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
After softening yeast in 1/4 cup warm water, add to make a soft dough.
Mix dough by 4 p.m.
Let rise until 7 p.m.
Punch down dough; let rise again.
Form into rolls by 10 p.m.
Bake in morning at 350°.
Good for dinner rolls, caramel rolls, coffee cake, hamburger buns, etc.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter until soft but not brown. Stir in barley; cook over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes, or until barley begins to brown.
Stir constantly.
Add hot consomme very slowly; barley will sizzle.
Cook over lowest heat until barley has absorbed liquid (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Saute mushrooms.
Put in barley and season.
Cook a few minutes together.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well for 2 minutes.
Follow baking instructions on cake mix box.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream cheese, margarine and sugar.
Mix alternately with flour, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Let cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Boil beets until done. Peel and slice. Put in boiler. Put even amount of vinegar and sugar over beets. Cover good. Use no water. Boil long enough to dissolve sugar. Seal in jars.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix the 3/4 cup of sugar with half of the cinnamon; roll the biscuit sections in the mixture and drop into Bundt pan.
Boil together 1 cup of sugar, the margarine, brown sugar, milk and the remaining cinnamon.
Pour over biscuit mixture and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hearty soup
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on each serving.
